// Indonesian-only, context-aware responses based on keywords

// Expanded Indonesian keyword responses - 50+ topics
const ID_RESPONSES = {
  // Emosi & Perasaan
  galau: "Merasa galau merupakan pengalaman manusiawi yang wajar, terutama ketika menghadapi situasi kompleks atau penuh ambiguitas. Perasaan ini menunjukkan Anda sedang memproses sesuatu penting. Berikut cara mengelolanya dengan sehat:\n\n1. Terima tanpa judgment. Galau bukan kelemahan, melainkan tanda bahwa Anda peduli dan berpikir mendalam. Jangan paksa diri untuk 'segera baik'.\n\n2. Journaling untuk clarity. Tulis apa yang membuat Anda galau tanpa sensor. Terkadang keraguan terlihat lebih jelas saat di tuangkan dalam kata-kata.\n\n3. Talk to someone you trust. Sharing dengan teman yang tidak menghakimi bisa memberikan perspektif baru. Jangan isolasi diri saat galau.\n\n4. Distract dengan aktivitas ringan. Baca buku, dengarkan musik, atau jalan-jalan sebentar untuk 'reset' pikiran.\n\n5. Set a decision deadline. Jika galau karena harus memilih, beri diri waktu terbatas untuk memutuskan, lalu commit dengan pilihan tersebut.\n\n6. Practice self-compassion. Bicara pada diri sendiri seperti Anda berbicara pada teman baik yang sedang galau.\n\nIngat, galau adalah sementara. Like clouds, it will pass.",
  sedih: "Kesedihan merupakan emosi yang valid dan bagian penting dari pengalaman manusia. Tidak ada yang salah dengan merasa sedih - ini menunjukkan kapasitas Anda untuk merasakan kedalaman emosi. Berikut cara menavigasinya:\n\n1. Allow yourself to feel. Jangan tahan atau invalidasi kesedihan Anda. Air mata dan rasa sedih adalah cara tubuh melepaskan beban emosional.\n\n2. Identify the source. Apa yang sebenarnya membuat Anda sedih? Kehilangan? Kekecewaan? Kesepian? Mengetahui akarnya membantu proses healing.\n\n3. Create a comfort routine. Siapkan 'emotional first aid kit': playlist favorit, film comfort, makanan hangat, atau aktivitas yang menenangkan.\n\n4. Reach out. Kesendirian memperburuk kesedihan. Hubungi satu orang yang Anda percaya, meski hanya untuk duduk diam bersama.\n\n5. Physical movement helps. Light exercise, yoga, atau sekadar jalan kaki bisa melepaskan endorphin dan mengurangi intensitas kesedihan.\n\n6. Seek professional help if needed. Jika kesedihan berkepanjangan dan mengganggu fungsi sehari-hari, konsultasi dengan psikolog adalah langkah berani dan bijak.\n\nIt's okay not to be okay. Healing takes time.",
  senang: "Kebahagiaan merupakan resource berharga yang layak dirayakan dan diperdalam. Ketika Anda merasa senang, ini kesempatan untuk membangun emotional resilience dan memperkuat relasi. Berikut cara memaksimalkan momen positif ini:\n\n1. Savor the moment. Jangan biarkan kebahagiaan lewat begitu saja. Fokus sepenuhnya pada pengalaman ini dengan mindfulness. Rasakan sensasinya, perhatikan detailnya, dan syukuri dengan tulus.\n\n2. Share dengan orang berarti. Kebahagiaan yang dibagikan berlipat ganda. Hubungi teman, keluarga, atau partner untuk berbagi kabar baik. Social connection memperkuat positive emotions.\n\n3. Document dengan bijak. Foto atau catatan singkat bisa menjadi 'happiness anchor' di masa depan. Tapi jangan sampai dokumentasi mengurangi kualitas pengalaman itu sendiri.\n\n4. Reflect on the source. Apa yang menyebabkan kebahagiaan ini? Memahami triggers positif membantu Anda menciptakan lebih banyak momen serupa di masa depan.\n\n5. Pay it forward. Gunakan energi positif ini untuk berbuat baik. Kebaikan yang diberikan dalam keadaan bahagia terasa lebih tulus dan berdampak lebih besar.\n\n6. Create memory markers. Asosiasikan kebahagiaan ini dengan sesuatu yang bisa Anda trigger di masa depan - lagu, tempat, atau ritual tertentu.\n\nHappiness is not just to be enjoyed, but to be cultivated and shared.",
  marah: "Kemarahan merupakan emosi yang powerful dan seringkali menandakan sesuatu yang penting bagi Anda telah dilanggar. Penting untuk mengelolanya dengan sehat agar tidak merusak relasi atau diri sendiri:\n\n1. Pause before reacting. Amarah dalam 6 detik pertama biasanya reaktif, bukan responsif. Tarik napas, keluar dari situasi sejenak sebelum bereaksi.\n\n2. Identify the trigger. Apa yang sebenarnya membuat Anda marah? Apakah itu disrespect, injustice, atau feeling powerless? Mengerti akarnya membantu.\n\n3. Express assertively, not aggressively. Gunakan 'I statements': 'Saya merasa... ketika... karena...' daripada menyalahkan atau menyerang.\n\n4. Physical outlet yang sehat. Olahraga intens, punching bag, atau bahkan teriakan di tempat sepi bisa melepaskan energi amarah tanpa konsekuensi negatif.\n\n5. Pick your battles. Tidak semua hal layak diperjuangkan dengan amarah. Tanyakan: 'Apakah ini penting 1 minggu dari sekarang?'\n\n6. Channel into action. Gunakan energi amarah untuk change yang konstruktif, bukan destructive. Amarah bisa menjadi fuel untuk activism atau improvement.\n\n7. Forgiveness is for you. Memaafkan bukan berarti membenarkan kesalahan, melainkan melepaskan beban amarah agar Anda bisa move forward.\n\nAnger is one letter short of danger. Manage it wisely.",
  cemas: "Kecemasan merupakan respons alami terhadap perceived threat atau uncertainty, tapi ketika berlebihan bisa mengganggu kualitas hidup. Berikut strategi evidence-based untuk mengelolanya:\n\n1. Grounding techniques (5-4-3-2-1 method). Identifikasi 5 hal yang Anda lihat, 4 yang Anda sentuh, 3 yang Anda dengar, 2 yang Anda cium, 1 yang Anda rasakan. Ini membawa Anda kembali ke present moment.\n\n2. Breathing exercises. Selain 4-7-8, coba box breathing: 4 detik inhale, 4 hold, 4 exhale, 4 hold. Repeat 5 kali.\n\n3. Challenge anxious thoughts. Tanyakan: 'Apa buktinya?' 'Apakah ini fact atau interpretation?' 'Apa yang paling buruk yang bisa terjadi, dan bisakah saya handle itu?'\n\n4. Limit stimulants. Kafein, gula berlebihan, dan lack of sleep memperburuk kecemasan. Perhatikan lifestyle factors.\n\n5. Scheduled worry time. Alih-alih cemas sepanjang hari, alokasikan 15 menit khusus untuk 'worry'. Di luar waktu itu, tulis saja dan 'tunda' ke waktu tersebut.\n\n6. Progressive muscle relaxation. Tegangkan dan relaksasikan setiap grup otot dari ujung kaki ke kepala. Ini melepaskan physical tension yang menyertai kecemasan.\n\n7. Seek professional support. CBT (Cognitive Behavioral Therapy) terbukti sangat efektif untuk anxiety disorders.\n\nAnxiety is like a rocking chair - it gives you something to do but doesn't get you anywhere.",
  bosan: "Kebosanan merupakan sinyal kompleks dari pikiran yang mengindikasikan berbagai hal: understimulation, kurangnya meaning, atau kebutuhan akan novelty. Jangan anggap remeh - bosan kronis bisa mengarah pada dissatisfaction yang lebih dalam. Berikut strategi mengubah bosan menjadi opportunity:\n\n1. Reinterpret boredom. Alih-alih melawan, lihat sebagai 'call for growth'. Pikiran bosan menunjukkan Anda siap untuk tantangan atau stimulation baru.\n\n2. Micro-adventure. Tidak perlu traveling jauh. Coba rute berbeda saat commute, kunjungi kafe baru di lingkungan, atau eksplorasi hobby yang belum pernah dicoba. Novelty dalam dosis kecil bisa sangat refreshing.\n\n3. Deep work shallow. Gunakan waktu bosan untuk tugas yang terabaikan: organize files, declutter space, atau maintenance task. Productive boredom adalah skill berharga.\n\n4. Creative output. Bosan bisa menjadi fuel untuk kreativitas. Menulis, menggambar, atau membuat musik tanpa tujuan tertentu sering menghasilkan hasil yang mengejutkan.\n\n5. Mindful idleness. Jangan langsung grab ponsel saat bosan. Biarkan pikiran mengembara tanpa stimulus eksternal. Daydreaming dan mind-wandering memiliki nilai kognitif yang terbukti.\n\n6. Connect dengan others. Reach out ke teman yang lama tidak dikontak, atau ajak rekan untuk casual conversation. Social interaction adalah antidote yang powerful untuk boredom.\n\n7. Learn something new. Platform seperti YouTube, Coursera, atau podcast bisa mengubah waktu bosan jadi investasi skill baru.\n\nBoredom is the mother of creativity - if you know how to channel it.",
  lelah: "Kelelahan merupakan sinyal penting dari sistem Anda yang menunjukkan ketidakseimbangan antara expenditure dan recovery. Dalam budaya yang mengagungkan hustle, istirahat sering dilihat sebagai kemalasan - padahal ini merupakan komponen esensial dari performance sustainable. Berikut pendekatan komprehensif untuk recovery:\n\n1. Identify fatigue type. Apakah ini physical fatigue (tubuh butuh istirahat), mental fatigue (pikiran butuh break), atau emotional fatigue (perasaan butuh processing)? Tiap tipe butuh strategi berbeda.\n\n2. Prioritize sleep quality. Tidur adalah fondasi pemulihan. 7-9 jam dengan sleep hygiene yang baik lebih berharga daripada 10 jam dengan kualitas buruk. Perhatikan circadian rhythm Anda.\n\n3. Strategic disconnection. Unplug dari work dan digital device. True rest membutuhkan cognitive detachment - tidak cek email, tidak scroll social media, tidak merencanakan task berikutnya.\n\n4. Active recovery. Jangan salah artikan istirahat sebagai immobility. Light exercise, stretching, yoga, atau jalan kaki santai sering lebih restorative daripada complete inactivity.\n\n5. Nutrition untuk recovery. Dehidrasi dan poor nutrition memperburuk kelelahan. Air putih yang cukup, protein untuk repair, dan complex carbs untuk energy restock adalah essential.\n\n6. Micro-rest sepanjang hari. Pomodoro technique, breathing breaks, atau 5-menit meditation setiap jam bisa mencegah fatigue accumulation.\n\n7. Re-evaluate workload. Jika kelelahan kronis, mungkin Anda over-committed. Audit commitments dan eliminasi atau delegate apa yang tidak esensial.\n\nRest is not the opposite of productivity - it is the foundation of sustainable high performance.",
  stress: "Stres merupakan respons fisiologis yang sebenarnya adaptif dan protective - masalahnya chronic stress dan poor stress management. Memahami mekanisme stres membantu Anda mengubahnya dari threat menjadi challenge yang bisa diatasi. Berikut framework evidence-based untuk mengelola stres:\n\n1. Reframe stress response. Tanda fisik stres (detak jantung meningkat, energi naik) adalah persiapan tubuh untuk action. View sebagai 'body energizing' daripada 'body malfunctioning'. Mindset ini sendiri mengurangi dampak negatif stres.\n\n2. Identify stressor patterns. Track stres Anda: kapan muncul, apa triggernya, intensitasnya, dan coping apa yang dicoba. Data ini mengungkap pattern dan memungkinkan intervention yang terarah.\n\n3. Problem-focused vs emotion-focused. Apakah stres ini bisa diubah (problem-focused coping: action untuk solve)? Atau harus diterima (emotion-focused coping: acceptance, support seeking)? Pilih strategi yang sesuai kontrol Anda.\n\n4. Physiological regulation. Stres adalah experience embodied. Techniques seperti deep breathing, progressive muscle relaxation, atau cold exposure bisa langsung menurunkan cortisol dan activate parasympathetic nervous system.\n\n5. Social buffering. Hubungan supportif adalah salah satu buffer stres yang paling powerful. Jangan isolasi diri - sharing load dengan trusted others mengurangi perceived burden.\n\n6. Nature exposure. Waktu di alam, bahkan 10-15 menit di taman, secara terbukti menurunkan stres hormone dan improve mood. Biophilia effect adalah real dan powerful.\n\n7. Micro-recovery practices. Integrasikan recovery ke throughout the day: music break, pet interaction, humor (laughing lowers stress), atau gratitude practice.\n\n8. Professional support. Jika stres mengganggu functioning atau persistent lebih dari beberapa minggu, konsultasi dengan psikolog atau counselor adalah langkah wise.\n\nStress is inevitable, but suffering from stress is optional.",
  takut: "Ketakutan merupakan respons evolusioner yang fundamental untuk survival - tapi dalam dunia modern, banyak ketakutan kita merupakan 'false alarms' yang menghambat growth dan opportunity. Memahami dan mengelola ketakutan merupakan keterampilan hidup yang esensial. Berikut pendekatan systematic untuk menghadapi ketakutan:\n\n1. Analyze fear rationally. Tanyakan: Apa yang sebenarnya saya takutkan? Seberapa realistis risikonya? Apa worst-case scenario yang bisa terjadi? Dan bisakah saya handle itu? Cognitive analysis sering mengurangi intensitas ketakutan irasional.\n\n2. Fear hierarchy exposure. Break down fear menjadi component kecil. Mulai dengan exposure paling ringan, master itu, lalu naik level. Desensitization bertahap adalah metode terbukti dalam behavior therapy.\n\n3. Courage vs confidence. Courage bukan berarti tidak takut - itu berarti action meski takut. Don't wait until confidence datang untuk act; action build confidence.\n\n4. Fear as information. Tanyakan apa yang bisa dipelajari dari ketakutan ini. Apakah ada genuine risk yang perlu di-mitigate? Apakah ada growth opportunity di ujung fear? Takut terkadang menunjukkan apa yang benar-benar penting bagi kita.\n\n5. Resource activation. Ketika takut, pikiran fokus pada threat. Sengaja redirect attention ke resources Anda: skills, support system, pengalaman masa lalu yang relevan, dan personal strengths.\n\n6. Mindfulness untuk anxiety. Grounding techniques membawa Anda kembali ke present moment ketika fear spiral menjadi catastrophic thinking. 5-4-3-2-1 technique atau box breathing bisa langsung menenangkan.\n\n7. Professional guidance untuk phobia. Jika fear adalah specific phobia (takut yang intens dan irrational terhadap objek/spesifik situasi), terapi profesional seperti CBT atau exposure therapy sangat efektif.\n\n8. Fear journal. Catat setiap kali Anda menghadapi fear dan bertahan. Review ini regularly akan membangun evidence bahwa Anda lebih capable daripada yang dipikirkan.\n\nFear is a compass showing you where growth awaits.",
  malas: "Procrastination dan 'malas' merupakan fenomena kompleks yang jarang tentang kemalasan murni. Research menunjukkan procrastination lebih sering disebabkan oleh emotional regulation issues (coping dengan negative mood associated dengan task) daripada time management issues. Berikut cara memahami dan mengatasi 'malas' dengan lebih effective:\n\n1. Investigate the root. Malas adalah symptom, bukan diagnosis. Apakah underlying cause adalah: fear of failure, task overwhelm, lack of clarity, low energy, perfectionism, atau values misalignment? Tiap cause butuh intervention berbeda.\n\n2. The 2-minute rule. Jika resistance tinggi, negotiat dengan diri sendiri untuk hanya 2 menit. 'Saya hanya akan buka dokumen'. Momentum sering mengambil alih setelah friction awal teratasi.\n\n3. Environment design. 'Malas' sering environment-driven. Buat starting action effortless: siapkan workspace sebelumnya, matikan distractions, atau gunakan accountability buddy.\n\n4. Focus on identity, not outcome. Alih-alih 'saya harus mengerjakan X', coba 'saya adalah tipe orang yang...'. Identity-based habits lebih sustainable karena mengubah self-concept.\n\n5. Temptation bundling. Pair task yang dihindari dengan activity yang dinikmati. Contoh: hanya boleh dengarkan podcast favorit saat jogging, atau nonton series saat folding laundry.\n\n6. Break the perfectionism-procrastination loop. Malas sering karena expectation terlalu tinggi. Lower the bar untuk start: draft jelek lebih baik daripada no draft. You can't edit a blank page.\n\n7. Strategic rest vs procrastination. Bedakan genuine need untuk recovery dengan avoidance. Jika memang butuh istirahat, rest intentionally dan guilt-free. Jika menghindari, gunakan technique di atas.\n\n8. Self-compassion, not self-criticism. Self-criticism memperburuk emotional state yang menyebabkan procrastination. Self-compassion mengurangi defensive avoidance dan membuat action lebih likely.\n\nLaziness is often a misunderstanding of the real barriers to action.",
  kecewa: "Kekecewaan merupakan emotional response terhadap unmet expectations - dan expectations merupakan bagian tak terpisahkan dari being human. Bagaimana Anda menavigasi kekecewaan menentukan apakah itu menjadi setback atau setup untuk growth. Berikut pendekatan constructive untuk processing disappointment:\n\n1. Validate the emotion. Kekecewaan adalah valid dan normal. Jangan toxic positivity diri sendiri dengan 'saya seharusnya tidak kecewa'. Allow yourself to feel without judgment.\n\n2. Distinguish types of disappointment. Apakah ini: situational (keadaan di luar kontrol), personal (kegagalan kita sendiri), atau relational (others letting us down)? Tiap tipe butuh different processing.\n\n3. Adjust expectations vs adjust reality. Kececewaan gap antara expectation dan reality. Evaluasi: Apakah expectation saya realistic? Jika ya, bagaimana reality bisa diimprove? Jika tidak, bagaimana adjust expectation?\n\n4. Learning extraction. Apa lesson yang bisa diambil? Apa yang akan saya lakukan berbeda? Frame disappointment sebagai data, bukan defeat. Setiap 'no' atau failure adalah information untuk next attempt.\n\n5. Grieving the loss. Kekecewaan sering melibatkan loss dari sesuatu yang diharapkan: opportunity, relationship phase, atau imagined future. Allow yourself to grieve this loss sebelum move on.\n\n6. Counterfactual thinking. 'At least...' thinking bisa mengurangi intensity kecewaan. At least saya mencoba. At least saya tahu sekarang. At least ada other opportunities.\n\n7. Re-engage intentionally. Jangan buru-buru 'move on' tanpa processing. Tapi juga jangan terjebak indefinitely. Set waktu untuk processing, lalu commit untuk forward action.\n\n8. Seek perspective. Talk dengan mentor atau trusted friend. Others sering melihat situation dengan lensa berbeda yang memperluas perspektif kita.\n\nDisappointment is the gap between what you expected and what you got. Narrow the gap by either adjusting expectations or improving reality.",
  bingung: "Kebingungan merupakan cognitive state yang menunjukkan Anda menghadapi complexity, ambiguity, atau conflicting information. Meski uncomfortable, kebingungan sering menandakan Anda sedang memproses sesuatu yang meaningful dan multifaceted. Berikut strategi untuk navigasi confusion menuju clarity:\n\n1. Accept confusion as normal. Jangan self-criticize karena bingung. Complexity adalah real dan menghadapinya dengan confusion adalah honest response, bukan kelemahan.\n\n2. Information audit. Apakah kebingungan karena information overload atau information insufficiency? Terlalu banyak data bisa paralyze sama dengan terlalu sedikit. Identify which one dan act accordingly.\n\n3. Break into components. Kehidupan, keputusan, atau problem besar sering overwhelming karena holistik. Break down menjadi smaller chunks yang bisa dianalisis satu per satu.\n\n4. Clarify criteria. Apa yang sebenarnya Anda prioritaskan? Decision-making menjadi lebih mudah ketika kriteria jelas. Rank your values untuk this specific context.\n\n5. Seek diverse perspectives. Talk dengan orang yang punya experience berbeda. Jangan hanya cari konfirmasi dari mereka yang setuju dengan Anda - seek constructive disagreement.\n\n6. Trial and error approach. Jika analysis paralysis, consider small experiment. Try one option in small scale, evaluate, adjust. Action menghasilkan clarity lebih dari thinking.\n\n7. Sleep on it. Incubation effect adalah real. Otak memproses informasi subconsciously. Decision yang dibuat setelah good rest dan fresh perspective sering lebih baik.\n\n8. Embrace 'good enough'. Tidak semua keputusan perlu perfect. Satisficing (memuaskan + cukup) sering lebih practical daripada optimizing, terutama untuk keputusan reversible.\n\nConfusion is the first step toward clarity.",
  kesepian: "Kesepian merupakan subjective distress yang muncul dari perceived gap antara desired and actual social connection. Ini berbeda dari solitude (being alone yang enjoyable) dan bisa terjadi bahkan saat surrounded by people. Kesepian yang persistent berdampak serius pada health, setara dengan smoking 15 cigarettes per day. Berikut pendekatan multifaceted untuk mengatasi kesepian:\n\n1. Distinguish types of loneliness. Apakah ini: intimate loneliness (kurang close relationship), relational loneliness (kurang quality friendships), atau collective loneliness (kurang sense of belonging ke community)? Tiap butuh strategi berbeda.\n\n2. Quality over quantity. Satu atau dua deep connection lebih berharga daripada banyak superficial relationships. Invest dalam quality time dengan existing relationships daripada chase banyak connection.\n\n3. Vulnerability as bridge. Kesepian sering diperpanjang karena kita tidak reveal true self. Practice vulnerability: share authentically, express needs, dan invite others to do the same.\n\n4. Structured social activities. Join groups dengan regular meetings: book club, running group, volunteer organization, atau class. Struktur mengurangkan effort untuk maintain contact dan build consistency.\n\n5. Service to others. Volunteer atau bantu orang lain. Helping behavior mengurangkan self-focus dan menciptakan connection meaning-based.\n\n6. Digital detox. Social media sering exacerbate loneliness dengan comparison dan superficial connection. Limit passive scrolling dan prioritize active, synchronous interaction.\n\n7. Reframe solitude. Develop capacity untuk enjoy your own company. Solitude yang comfortable adalah foundation untuk healthy relationship dengan others.\n\n8. Professional support. Jika kesepian chronic dan menyebabkan significant distress, therapy bisa membantu unpack underlying patterns dan build social skills.\n\nLoneliness is the poverty of self; solitude is the richness of self.",
  iri: "Rasa iri merupakan emosi yang sering maligned padahal secara functional memberi informasi berharga tentang apa yang kita value dan desire. Iri merupakan social emotion yang muncul dari comparison, tapi bisa diubah dari poison menjadi compass untuk growth. Berikut cara mengelola dan memanfaatkan iri dengan constructive:\n\n1. Decode the envy. Apa yang sebenarnya Anda iri? Apakah posisi mereka, sifat mereka, atau outcome mereka? Specificity mengungkap true desire di balik surface-level jealousy.\n\n2. Inspiration, not competition. Reframe: 'Jika mereka bisa, itu bukti saya juga bisa' daripada 'Mereka punya, saya tidak'. Abundance mindset mengubah zero-sum menjadi possibility.\n\n3. Compare dengan diri sendiri. Growth yang sebenarnya adalah personal progress over time, bukan comparison dengan others. Track your own metrics dan celebrate personal milestones.\n\n4. Behind-the-scenes reality. Apa yang Anda iri adalah highlight reel, bukan behind-the-scenes. Orang yang Anda iri punya struggles, sacrifices, dan insecurities yang tidak terlihat.\n\n5. Count your own blessings. Gratitude practice mengurangi comparison tendencies. Listing apa yang Anda syukuri shift fokus dari lack ke abundance.\n\n6. Compliment, don't compete. Ucapkan genuine compliment kepada yang Anda iri. This kills envy dan menciptakan connection. Mereka mungkin bahkan sharing how they achieved it.\n\n7. Action over rumination. Jika iri menunjukkan legitimate desire, gunakan sebagai motivation untuk action. What concrete step bisa Anda ambil menuju hal serupa?\n\n8. Self-compassion. Iri sering disertai self-criticism. Be kind pada diri sendiri. You are on your own path dengan unique timeline dan circumstances.\n\nEnvy is ignorance of your own journey.",
  cinta: "Cinta romantis merupakan experience yang profound namun sering idealized dalam culture. Hubungan yang healthy dan lasting membutuhkan lebih dari chemistry dan attraction - mereka membutuhkan intentional work, compatibility, dan shared growth mindset. Berikut framework untuk relationship yang fulfilling dan sustainable:\n\n1. Foundation of friendship. Research consistently menunjukkan bahwa best romantic relationships dibangun di atas strong friendship. Mutual respect, trust, dan genuine liking adalah non-negotiable base.\n\n2. Secure attachment cultivation. Secure attachment relationship dicirikan oleh: emotional availability, responsiveness, consistency, dan comfort with intimacy. Jika attachment Anda anxious atau avoidant, self-awareness dan communication bisa membantu move toward security.\n\n3. Conflict as opportunity. Healthy couples don't avoid conflict - they navigate it well. Learn constructive conflict: focus on issue bukan personal attack, use 'I' statements, seek understanding bukan victory, dan repair setelah argument.\n\n4. Love languages awareness. Understanding bagaimana Anda dan partner express dan receive love (words of affirmation, acts of service, receiving gifts, quality time, physical touch) bisa mengeliminasi banyak miscommunication.\n\n5. Interdependence over codependence. Healthy relationship adalah interdependent: two whole individuals choosing to share life, bukan two halves completing each other. Maintain individual identity, interests, dan growth.\n\n6. Regular relationship maintenance. Check-in rutin tentang relationship satisfaction, unmet needs, dan appreciation. Don't wait for crisis untuk invest in relationship.\n\n7. Shared meaning dan goals. Long-term compatibility membutuhkan alignment dalam values, life vision, dan fundamental goals. Diskusikan ini early dan regularly.\n\n8. Intentional appreciation. Negativity bias membuat kita fokus pada flaws. Counter dengan intentional gratitude practice: recognize dan verbalize apa yang Anda appreciate tentang partner secara regular.\n\nLove is a verb - it's what you do consistently, not just what you feel.",
  putus: "Putus cinta merupakan loss yang significant - otak memprosesnya mirip dengan drug withdrawal karena romantic love activate reward circuitry yang sama. Proses grieving merupakan hal yang necessary dan tidak ada timeline yang 'benar'. Bagaimana Anda menavigasi ini menentukan apakah itu menjadi trauma atau transformation. Berikut pendekatan untuk healing yang healthy:\n\n1. Honor the grief. Allow yourself untuk merasa sakit tanpa judgment. Breakup involves loss dari: partner, shared identity, future yang dibayangkan, dan routine. Mourn these losses fully.\n\n2. No contact rule. Cut contact (termasuk social media stalking) adalah krusial untuk healing. Setiap 'check' memperpanjang withdrawal dan memperkuat neural pathway yang ingin Anda rewire.\n\n3. Narrative reconstruction. Jangan idealize relationship. Write honest account: apa yang tidak beres, red flags, incompatibility, dan kenapa breakup adalah necessary. Realistic narrative membantu move on.\n\n4. Identity rebuilding. Relationship sering mengaburkan individual identity. Reconnect dengan who you are outside relationship: hobi lama, friendships, personal goals, dan values.\n\n5. Self-compassion over self-criticism. Jangan self-blame untuk breakup atau obsesi tentang 'what I did wrong'. Most relationships end karena incompatibility, bukan deficiency.\n\n6. Support system activation. Lean on friends dan family. Isolation memperburuk depressive symptoms yang sering follow breakup. Social support adalah buffer yang powerful.\n\n7. Growth reflection. Apa yang dipelajari? Bagaimana Anda berkembang? Apa yang tidak akan Anda tolerasi di relationship berikutnya? Reflection turn pain into wisdom.\n\n8. New meaning dan purpose. Gunakan energy dan waktu yang sebelumnya diinvestasikan dalam relationship untuk self-development, new projects, atau helping others.\n\n9. Future openness. Jangan rush ke relationship baru untuk fill void (rebound). Tapi juga jangan jaded tentang love. Heal fully, lalu open dengan wisdom baru.\n\nBreakups are hard because you didn't just lose love, you lost the future you thought you'd have.",

  // Kesehatan & Wellness
  sehat: "Menjaga kesehatan tubuh merupakan foundation untuk performa optimal dalam segala aspek hidup. Ini rekomendasi praktis yang terbukti secara ilmiah:\n\n1. Move your body daily. Tidak harus gym - jalan kaki 30 menit, naik turun tangga, atau stretching saat break sudah beneficial. Yang penting konsisten, bukan intensitas.\n\n2. Prioritize sleep hygiene. 7-9 jam tidur berkualitas memulihkan otak dan tubuh. Hindari screen 1 jam sebelum tidur, jadikan kamar gelap dan dingin, dan hindari kafein setelah jam 2 sore.\n\n3. Nutrition over diet. Fokus pada whole foods (sayur, protein, healthy fats, complex carbs) daripada menghitung kalori obsesif. 80/20 rule: 80% nutritious, 20% whatever you want.\n\n4. Hydration matters. 8 gelas sehari membantu fungsi otak, energi, dan kulit. Bawa botol kemana-mana dan minum sebelum haus.\n\n5. Mental health affects physical health. Stress kronis bisa menyebabkan sakit fisik. Praktikkan mindfulness, meditasi, atau journaling untuk mental well-being.\n\n6. Preventive care penting. Check-up rutin, vaksinasi, dan screening sesuai usia bisa deteksi masalah sebelum parah. Jangan tunggu sakit untuk peduli kesehatan.\n\n7. Listen to your body. Fatigue, sakit kepala terus-menerus, atau mood swing bisa jadi tanda tubuh butuh rest atau evaluasi lifestyle.\n\nHealth is wealth - tanpa kesehatan, segala achievement terasa hollow.",
  sakit: "Saat tubuh sakit, itu merupakan sinyal bahwa sistem Anda butuh perhatian dan pemulihan. Menghormati sinyal ini merupakan bentuk self-care yang penting:\n\n1. Prioritaskan istirahat total. Tubuh membutuhkan energy untuk fight infection atau healing. Jangan paksa bekerja dengan performa rendah - itu justru memperpanjang waktu sakit.\n\n2. Hydration adalah key. Cairan yang cukup membantu mengeluarkan toxin, menjaga suhu tubuh, dan mencegah dehidrasi yang bisa memperburuk kondisi.\n\n3. Nutritious food, bukan comfort food berlebihan. Fokus pada makanan rich in vitamins, protein untuk repair, dan anti-inflammatory foods.\n\n4. Listen to your body's signals. Demam, nyeri, atau fatigue adalah cara tubuh berkomunikasi. Jangan mask symptoms dengan medication tanpa address underlying cause.\n\n5. Create healing environment. Kamar yang bersih, cukup ventilasi, dan nyaman membantu pemulihan. Jangan underestimate power of good sleep environment.\n\n6. Know when to seek help. Jika symptoms persist lebih dari 3 hari, intensitas meningkat, atau ada red flag symptoms, jangan ragu konsultasi dokter. Early detection saves lives.\n\n7. Mental health affects physical recovery. Stress atau anxiety bisa menurunkan immune system. Practice relaxation techniques saat sakit.\n\nYour body is your permanent home. Take care of it.",
  makan: "Nutrisi berfungsi sebagai fuel untuk body dan brain. Pola makan yang tepat bukan tentang restriction, melainkan nourishment yang sustainable:\n\n1. Prioritize whole foods. Sayur, buah, protein, dan whole grains harus menjadi majority dari plate Anda. Processed foods minimalkan, bukan eliminasi total.\n\n2. Protein di setiap makan. Protein membangun tissue, mengatur hormone, dan menjaga kenyang lebih lama. Target 20-30g protein per makan.\n\n3. Healthy fats are essential. Alpukat, kacang, minyak zaitun, dan ikan berlemak mendukung brain function dan hormone health.\n\n4. Mindful eating. Makan tanpa distraction, kunyah perlahan, dan listen to hunger cues. Stop saat 80% full, bukan saat overstuffed.\n\n5. Hydration first. Dehidrasi sering disalahartikan sebagai lapar. Minum air sebelum makan dan bawa botol kemana-mana.\n\nFood is medicine when chosen wisely.",
  tidur: "Sleep merupakan biological necessity, bukan luxury. Kualitas tidur yang buruk mempengaruhi segala aspek: mood, cognitive function, immune system, bahkan weight management. Berikut sleep hygiene yang terbukti:\n\n1. Consistent sleep schedule. Bangun dan tidur di jam yang sama setiap hari, termasuk weekend. Ini mengatur circadian rhythm Anda.\n\n2. Wind-down routine 30-60 menit sebelum tidur. Matikan gadget, coba stretching ringan, membaca buku fisik, atau meditasi. Blue light mengganggu melatonin production.\n\n3. Optimize sleep environment. Kamar harus gelap (gunakan blackout curtains), dingin (18-22°C ideal), dan tenang. Consider white noise machine jika environment bising.\n\n4. Limit caffeine dan heavy meals. Hindari kafein setelah jam 2 sore dan makanan berat 3 jam sebelum tidur. Digestion mengganggu sleep quality.\n\n5. Bed is for sleep only. Jangan kerja, nonton, atau scroll social media di tempat tidur. Ini membuat brain associate bed dengan wakefulness.\n\n6. Manage worry before bed. Jika pikiran berkecamuk, tulis di jurnal untuk 'park' thoughts sampai besok. Mindfulness atau progressive relaxation bisa membantu.\n\n7. Nap strategically. Jika perlu siang, batasi 20-30 menit sebelum jam 3 sore. Long naps atau late naps mengganggu nighttime sleep.\n\nSleep is the foundation of health. Protect it fiercely.",
  olahraga: "Movement merupakan medicine yang paling powerful dan accessible. Regular exercise tidak hanya untuk physical fitness, tapi juga mental health, cognitive function, dan longevity. Berikut cara membuatnya sustainable:\n\n1. Find your why beyond aesthetics. Fokus pada energy, mood, strength, atau longevity daripada sekadar penampilan. Intrinsic motivation lasts longer.\n\n2. Start ridiculously small. 5 menit jalan kaki lebih baik dari rencana 1 jam gym yang tidak terlaksana. Build habit dulu, intensity menyusul.\n\n3. Choose enjoyable activities. Jika benci gym, jangan paksa. Coba dance, hiking, swimming, martial arts, atau olahraga tim. Enjoyment drives consistency.\n\n4. Schedule seperti meeting. Block waktu di calendar dan treat sebagai non-negotiable appointment dengan diri sendiri.\n\n5. Incorporate movement into daily life. Naik tangga, berdiri saat meeting, jalan kaki untuk meeting, atau stretching breaks setiap jam. NEAT (Non-Exercise Activity Thermogenesis) penting.\n\n6. Recovery is part of training. Jangan olahraga setiap hari tanpa rest. Sleep, nutrition, dan active recovery sama pentingnya dengan workout itu sendiri.\n\n7. Track progress untuk motivation. Catat improvements: bisa jalan lebih jauh, angkat lebih berat, atau sekadar mood yang lebih baik. Progress adalah motivator terbaik.\n\nThe best workout is the one you'll actually do consistently.",
  diet: "Approach diet dengan mindset sustainability, bukan quick fix. Diet yang berhasil merupakan yang bisa dijalankan seumur hidup, bukan 30 hari:\n\n1. 80/20 principle. 80% nutritious whole foods, 20% flexibility untuk treat. Perfectionism dalam diet sering backfire menjadi binge.\n\n2. Calorie awareness, not obsession. Understanding portion sizes lebih penting daripada menghitung setiap kalori. Plate method: ½ sayur, ¼ protein, ¼ karbohidrat.\n\n3. Jangan skip protein dan fiber. Keduanya adalah key untuk satiety. Diet yang membuat Anda lapar terus-menerus tidak sustainable.\n\n4. Planning prevents poor choices. Meal prep atau planning mengurangi reliance pada convenient but unhealthy options saat lapar.\n\n5. Progress, not perfection. One 'bad' meal tidak merusak progress. Consistency over weeks dan months adalah yang matters.\n\nThe best diet is the one you don't know you're on.",
  gemuk: "Weight management merupakan holistic process melibatkan nutrition, movement, sleep, dan stress management. Fokus pada health markers, bukan hanya scale:\n\n1. Sustainable caloric deficit. Defisit 300-500 kalori perhari lebih sustainable daripada crash diet. Target 0.5-1% body weight loss per minggu.\n\n2. Prioritize protein dan resistance training. Kombinasi ini mempertahankan muscle mass saat fat loss, menjaga metabolism tetap tinggi.\n\n3. NEAT matters. Non-Exercise Activity Thermogenesis (jalan, berdiri, gerakan harian) sering lebih berdampak dari workout singkat.\n\n4. Sleep dan stress management. Poor sleep dan chronic stress meningkatkan kortisol dan cravings, membuat weight loss lebih sulit.\n\n5. Track non-scale victories. Energy level, sleep quality, how clothes fit, dan fitness improvement sering lebih meaningful daripada angka di timbangan.\n\nHealth at every size is valid, but metabolic health matters.",
  kurus: "Weight gain yang healthy berkisar pada building lean mass, bukan just adding fat. Approach ini memastikan weight gain sustainable dan functionally beneficial:\n\n1. Caloric surplus terkontrol. Surplus 300-500 kalori perhari cukup untuk gain 0.25-0.5% body weight per minggu. Surplus berlebihan justru membuat fat gain berlebih.\n\n2. Prioritize protein (1.6-2.2g per kg bodyweight). Protein adalah building block untuk muscle growth. Distribute evenly sepanjang hari.\n\n3. Progressive resistance training. Weight gain tanpa strength training justru menjadi fat gain. Focus pada compound movements: squat, deadlift, bench, rows.\n\n4. Nutrient-dense calorie sources. Alpukat, kacang, oat, telur, dan full-fat dairy memberi kalori plus micronutrients. Avoid empty calories dari junk food.\n\n5. Consistency dan patience. Muscle building takes time. Track progress monthly, not daily. Celebrate strength gains sebagai leading indicator.\n\nStrong is the new healthy.",
  kulit: "Skin health merupakan inside-out process. Apa yang Anda konsumsi dan bagaimana Anda hidup lebih berdampak daripada skincare routine yang kompleks:\n\n1. Sun protection adalah non-negotiable. UV damage adalah penyebab utama premature aging dan skin cancer. SPF 30+ setiap hari, rain or shine.\n\n2. Nutrition for glow. Vitamin C, E, zinc, omega-3, dan antioxidants dari dalam mendukung collagen production dan skin repair.\n\n3. Hydration inside-out. Air yang cukup dan moisturizer eksternal bekerja bersama. Dehidrasi membuat kulit terlihat dull dan memperjelas fine lines.\n\n4. Sleep is repair time. 7-9 jam tidur memungkinkan skin cell regeneration. Beauty sleep adalah real phenomenon.\n\n5. Simple routine konsisten beats complex sporadic. Cleanser, moisturizer, sunscreen adalah foundation. Add actives (retinoid, vitamin C) satu per satu.\n\nYour skin is a reflection of your lifestyle.",
  mental: "Mental health merupakan foundation untuk overall wellbeing. Sama seperti physical health, mental health memerlukan maintenance, attention, dan professional care saat diperlukan:\n\n1. Destigmatize seeking help. Therapy dan konsultasi psikolog adalah self-care, bukan tanda kelemahan. Early intervention prevents escalation.\n\n2. Daily mental hygiene. Journaling, meditation, gratitude practice, atau mindfulness 10-15 menit perhari membangun resilience.\n\n3. Boundaries are protection. Learn to say no, disconnect dari toxicity, dan prioritize self-preservation. Boundary adalah skill, bukan selfishness.\n\n4. Connection is medicine. Strong social support adalah buffer terhadap stress dan depression. Invest dalam meaningful relationships.\n\n5. Mind-body connection. Exercise, sleep, dan nutrition mempengaruhi mental health. Holistic approach mencakup semua aspek.\n\nMental health is not a destination, but a process.",

  // Pekerjaan & Karir
  kerja: "Meningkatkan produktivitas kerja bukan tentang bekerja lebih lama, melainkan bekerja lebih cerdas. Berikut strategi proven untuk performa optimal:\n\n1. Eat the frog first. Kerjakan tugas paling sulit dan penting di pagi hari ketika willpower masih penuh. Menunda tugas besar justru membuat anxiety seharian.\n\n2. Time-blocking technique. Jadwalkan setiap jam di calendar Anda dengan blok spesifik untuk task tertentu. Ini mengurangi decision fatigue dan context-switching yang boros energi.\n\n3. Pomodoro untuk deep work. 25 menit fokus tanpa distraksi, lalu break 5 menit. Setelah 4 cycle, break 15-30 menit. Timer membuat kita accountable.\n\n4. The 2-minute rule. Kalau sesuatu bisa dikerjakan dalam 2 menit, lakukan sekarang. Jangan biarkan small tasks menumpuk jadi beban mental.\n\n5. Eliminate distractions. Matikan notifikasi non-urgent, gunakan website blocker, dan komunikasikan ke rekan kerja tentang 'focus hours' Anda.\n\n6. Learn to say no. Setiap 'yes' terhadap task baru adalah 'no' terhadap task existing. Prioritaskan berdasarkan impact, bukan urgensi semata.\n\n7. Rest is productive. Productivity decreases setelah 50-60 jam kerja seminggu. Breaks, hiburan, dan tidur cukup justru membuat Anda lebih kreatif dan efisien.\n\nProductivity is about being effective, not busy. Focus on outcomes, not hours logged.",
  karir: "Career development merupakan marathon, bukan sprint. Membangun karir yang fulfilling membutuhkan strategi jangka panjang, continuous learning, dan adaptabilitas. Berikut framework untuk pertumbuhan karir yang sustainable:\n\n1. Self-assessment yang jujur. Identifikasi strengths, weaknesses, values, dan interests Anda. Karir yang cocok adalah intersection antara what you're good at, what you love, dan what the world needs.\n\n2. Set clear career goals. Gunakan framework 3-5-10 tahun: posisi apa dalam 3 tahun? Industry apa dalam 5 tahun? Legacy apa dalam 10 tahun? Goals yang jelas membantu decision-making.\n\n3. Invest dalam skill building. Hard skills (technical) membuat Anda hired, soft skills (communication, leadership) membuat Anda promoted. Keduanya penting untuk long-term success.\n\n4. Find mentors and sponsors. Mentor memberi advice dan guidance; sponsors membuka doors dan advocate untuk Anda. Keduanya krusial untuk accelerasi karir.\n\n5. Build your personal brand. Showcase expertise melalui writing, speaking, atau contributing to projects. Reputasi yang kuat membuka opportunity tanpa Anda harus apply.\n\n6. Network strategically. Quality over quantity. Bangun relasi yang genuine dan mutually beneficial, bukan transactional connections.\n\n7. Take calculated risks. Pindah role, switch industry, atau ambil challenging assignment. Comfort zone adalah enemy of growth.\n\nCareer success is about direction, not speed.",
  wawancara: "Interview merupakan sales process di mana produknya Anda. Persiapan yang matang bisa membuat perbedaan antara 'meh' candidate dan 'must hire'. Berikut strategi untuk interview yang sukses:\n\n1. Research secara mendalam. Pahami company culture, recent news, products, competitors, dan challenges mereka. Gunakan LinkedIn untuk riset interviewer.\n\n2. Master the STAR method. Untuk behavioral questions (Tell me about a time when...), gunakan Situation-Task-Action-Result. Specificity adalah kunci.\n\n3. Prepare your value proposition. Apa yang membuat Anda unique? Highlight 3-4 key strengths dengan bukti konkrit. Jangan generic seperti 'saya rajin'.\n\n4. Anticipate tough questions. Siapkan jawaban untuk: weaknesses, gap dalam resume, kenapa pindah, dan salary expectations. Jangan defensive, be honest dengan growth mindset.\n\n5. Ask insightful questions. Interview adalah two-way street. Tanyakan tentang team dynamics, success metrics, growth opportunities, atau challenges dalam role tersebut.\n\n6. Practice out loud. Rehearse dengan teman atau di depan mirror. Record diri Anda untuk lihat body language dan filler words (um, like, you know).\n\n7. Follow up dengan gratitude email. Send personalized thank-you note dalam 24 jam, referensi spesifik dari conversation, dan reiterate interest.\n\nRemember: You are interviewing them as much as they are interviewing you.",
  resign: "Resign merupakan career transition yang perlu dikelola dengan professional dan strategic. Cara Anda keluar mempengaruhi reputasi dan future opportunities:\n\n1. Evaluate dengan matang. Pastikan keputusan bukan emosional impulse. List pros cons, dan punya plan B sebelum announce.\n\n2. Timing matters. Umumkan setelah project besar selesai, bukan saat tim dalam krisis. Standard notice period adalah 30 hari, lebih baik lebih.\n\n3. Conversation yang professional. Jadwalkan private meeting dengan atasan. Fokus pada gratitude dan growth, bukan complaint atau burning bridges.\n\n4. Document dan handover. Buat transition plan, dokumentasi processes, dan training successor. Leave dengan reputation intact.\n\n5. Maintain relationships. Network dengan rekan kerja, minta LinkedIn recommendations, dan jaga kontak. Dunia karir adalah kecil, reputation travels.\n\nLeave gracefully, your reputation follows you.",
  bisnis: "Entrepreneurship merupakan journey yang membutuhkan resilience, adaptability, dan execution discipline. Ide bagus tidak cukup, execution merupakan everything:\n\n1. Validate before building. Jangan buat produk dulu baru cari market. Test demand dengan MVP, landing pages, atau pre-orders sebelum invest besar.\n\n2. Know your numbers. Unit economics, cash flow, dan runway adalah vital signs bisnis. Financial literacy bukan optional untuk founder.\n\n3. Customer obsession. Listen to customers lebih banyak dari competitor analysis. Feedback adalah fuel untuk product-market fit.\n\n4. Iterate fast. Fail fast, learn faster. Pivot bukan kegagalan, melainkan strategic adjustment berdasarkan learning.\n\n5. Build strong team. Solo founder bisa survive, tapi great team scales. Hire untuk culture fit dan complementary skills.\n\nBusiness is about solving problems profitably.",
  gaji: "Salary negotiation merupakan business conversation, bukan personal request. Approach dengan data, timing, dan value proposition yang solid:\n\n1. Research market rate. Gunakan platform seperti Glassdoor, PayScale, atau survey industry untuk mengetahui range sesuai role, experience, dan lokasi.\n\n2. Quantify your value. List specific accomplishments dengan metrics: revenue generated, cost saved, efficiency improved. Numbers strengthen your case.\n\n3. Timing is strategic. Best time adalah saat performance review, after major win, atau saat offered new responsibility. Avoid saat company struggling.\n\n4. Consider total compensation. Base salary hanya satu komponen. Evaluate bonus, equity, benefits, remote flexibility, dan growth opportunity.\n\n5. Practice the conversation. Rehearse dengan friend atau mentor. Confidence dan clarity dalam delivery mempengaruhi outcome.\n\nKnow your worth, then ask for it.",
  atasan: "Managing up merupakan skill krusial untuk career advancement. Hubungan yang productive dengan atasan mempercepat growth dan opportunity:\n\n1. Understand their priorities. Apa yang penting bagi atasan Anda? Alignment dengan their goals membuat Anda valuable dan visible.\n\n2. Proactive communication. Jangan tunggu diminta update. Regular check-ins, progress reports, dan early warning saat ada issue.\n\n3. Bring solutions, not just problems. Saat raise concern, sertakan potential solutions. Shows critical thinking dan ownership.\n\n4. Ask for specific feedback. General 'how am I doing?' kurang useful. Tanyakan: 'What should I start/stop/continue doing?'\n\n5. Deliver consistently. Reliability builds trust. Meet deadlines, keep commitments, dan exceed expectations periodically.\n\nMake your boss look good, and you'll both succeed.",

  // Pendidikan & Belajar
  belajar: "Lifelong learning merupakan competitive advantage di era yang berubah cepat. Effective learning bukan tentang menghabiskan waktu paling banyak, melainkan menggunakan strategi yang terbukti secara kognitif. Berikut science-based learning techniques:\n\n1. Active recall, not passive re-reading. Test yourself secara aktif daripada membaca ulang. Flashcards, practice tests, atau menjelaskan konsep ke orang lain lebih efektif.\n\n2. Spaced repetition. Review materi pada interval yang meningkat (1 hari, 3 hari, 1 minggu, 1 bulan). Ini memperkuat neural pathways lebih baik daripada cramming.\n\n3. Interleaving practice. Jangan latihan satu topik terus-menerus. Campur berbagai tipe problems untuk memaksa otak adaptasi dan membedakan konsep.\n\n4. Elaborative interrogation. Tanyakan 'why' dan 'how' secara konstan. Hubungkan konsep baru dengan knowledge yang sudah ada.\n\n5. Concrete examples. Abstract concepts lebih mudah dipahami dengan contoh konkrit dan real-world applications.\n\n6. Dual coding. Kombinasikan words dengan visuals (diagrams, mind maps, sketches). Otak memproses informasi visual lebih efisien.\n\n7. Teach others. The protégé effect: mengajar orang lain memaksa Anda menguasai materi lebih dalam dan mengidentifikasi gaps dalam understanding.\n\nLearning is not about time spent, but about strategies used.",
  ujian: "Exam success berkisar pada preparation strategy, bukan cramming semalam. Spaced repetition dan active recall lebih efektif daripada passive re-reading:\n\n1. Start early, study smart. Distributed practice selama beberapa minggu mengalahkan cramming dalam retensi jangka panjang.\n\n2. Active recall technique. Test yourself dengan flashcards atau practice questions. Merecall informasi dari memory strengthen neural pathways.\n\n3. Simulate exam conditions. Latihan dengan time limit dan environment mirip ujian mengurangi anxiety dan meningkatkan performance.\n\n4. Prioritize sleep before exam. Tidur yang cukup lebih berharga daripada begadang belajar. Sleep consolidates memory dan improves cognitive function.\n\n5. Strategic approach saat ujian. Baca semua pertanyaan dulu, mulai dari yang paling mudah, dan manage waktu dengan bijak.\n\nPreparation beats last-minute panic.",
  skripsi: "Thesis merupakan marathon akademik yang membutuhkan project management, resilience, dan systematic approach. Break down menjadi manageable chunks untuk menghindari overwhelm:\n\n1. Create realistic timeline. Milestone jelas dengan buffer untuk unexpected delays. Weekly goals lebih effective daripada vague 'finish thesis soon'.\n\n2. Consistent daily progress. 2-3 hours fokus setiap hari mengalahkan sporadic all-nighters. Momentum builds consistency.\n\n3. Regular supervisor consultation. Jangan tunggu perfection untuk meet. Feedback early prevents major revisions later.\n\n4. Write terrible first draft. Perfectionism adalah enemy of progress. Get words down first, refine later. Editing easier dari writing from scratch.\n\n5. Self-care matters. Isolation dan burnout tidak produktif. Maintain social connection, exercise, dan sleep untuk sustainable productivity.\n\nDone is better than perfect.",
  kuliah: "University merupakan transformative period untuk intellectual growth, social development, dan career preparation. Manfaatkan holistically, bukan hanya untuk degree:\n\n1. Explore beyond major. Ambil elective courses dari berbagai disiplin. Interdisciplinary knowledge membuat Anda unique di job market.\n\n2. Build genuine relationships. Professors, peers, dan alumni adalah network berharga. Quality interactions lebih penting daripada jumlah connection.\n\n3. Develop soft skills. Organisasi, leadership, communication, dan teamwork skills dibangun through extracurriculars, bukan classroom semata.\n\n4. Seek experiences. Internships, research projects, study abroad, atau volunteer work provide practical learning dan resume building.\n\n5. Find your passion. College adalah safe space untuk explore. Coba berbagai hal untuk discover apa yang truly excites you.\n\nCollege is what you make of it.",
  sekolah: "School years membangun foundation untuk lifelong learning dan character development. Balance akademik dengan growth secara keseluruhan:\n\n1. Growth mindset over fixed grades. Intelligence bisa dikembangkan. Effort dan persistence lebih penting daripada 'natural talent'.\n\n2. Build study habits. Consistent routine, organized notes, dan active engagement dalam kelas adalah skills transferable ke jenjang berikutnya.\n\n3. Explore extracurriculars. Sports, arts, clubs membentuk teamwork, creativity, dan time management. Well-rounded lebih berharga daripada grade sempurna.\n\n4. Positive peer influence. Pilih teman yang supportive dan growth-oriented. Toxic friendships bisa menghambat development.\n\n5. Character matters most. Integrity, kindness, dan resilience adalah foundation untuk success in life, bukan sekadar report card.\n\nSchool is preparation for life, not just exams.",
  bahasa: "Language learning merupakan skill acquisition yang membutuhkan immersion, consistency, dan courage untuk make mistakes. There's no shortcut, tapi ada methods yang accelerate progress:\n\n1. Daily exposure adalah key. 15-30 menit setiap hari mengalahkan 3 jam sekali seminggu. Consistency builds neural pathways.\n\n2. Input comprehensible. Start dengan content yang Anda mostly understand. Gradually increase difficulty. i+1 principle: slightly above current level.\n\n3. Speak from day one. Jangan tunggu 'ready'. Making mistakes adalah bagian learning. Language partner atau tutor membantu overcome fear.\n\n4. Immerse in culture. Tonton shows, dengarkan music, baca books dalam target language. Context membuat vocabulary stick.\n\n5. Focus on communication, not perfection. Fluency lebih penting daripada grammatical perfection. Native speakers appreciate effort over accuracy.\n\nLanguages open doors to new worlds.",

  // Keuangan
  uang: "Personal finance merupakan life skill yang tidak diajarkan di sekolah, tapi berdampak besar pada quality of life. Financial wellbeing bukan tentang income tertinggi, melainkan management terbaik. Berikut framework yang terbukti:\n\n1. Track every expense. Awareness adalah langkah pertama. Gunakan apps atau spreadsheet untuk mencatat semua pengeluaran selama 30 hari. You'll be surprised where your money actually goes.\n\n2. Apply the 50/30/20 rule sebagai starting point. 50% untuk needs (housing, food, transport), 30% untuk wants (entertainment, dining out), 20% untuk savings dan debt repayment. Sesuaikan dengan situasi Anda.\n\n3. Build emergency fund dulu. Prioritaskan 3-6 bulan pengeluaran di savings yang accessible. Ini adalah safety net untuk unexpected events seperti job loss atau medical emergency.\n\n4. Automate your savings. Set automatic transfer di payday. Jika Anda tidak melihat uangnya, Anda tidak akan mengeluarkannya. Pay yourself first.\n\n5. Manage debt strategically. List semua utang dengan interest rates. Prioritaskan bayar high-interest debt (credit cards) lebih dulu sambil membayar minimum untuk lainnya.\n\n6. Diversify income streams. Relying on satu sumber income adalah risky. Explore side hustles, passive income, atau investasi untuk financial security.\n\n7. Invest in financial education. Baca buku personal finance, follow reputable financial advisors, dan terus belajar tentang money management.\n\nFinancial freedom is a journey, not a destination.",
  tabungan: "Saving berfungsi sebagai foundation financial health. Consistency lebih penting daripada amount - small habits compound menjadi significant results:\n\n1. Pay yourself first. Automate transfer saat gajian masuk, bukan sisa di akhir bulan. Behavioral finance: invisible money tidak ter-spend.\n\n2. Emergency fund priority. 3-6 months expenses adalah cushion untuk job loss, medical emergency, atau unexpected repairs. Keep liquid dan accessible.\n\n3. Goal-based buckets. Separate accounts untuk different goals: vacation, down payment, education. Mental accounting membantu discipline.\n\n4. Automate dan forget. Standing instruction atau auto-debit menghilangkan willpower fatigue. Set it once, benefit forever.\n\n5. Increase gradually. Saat gaji naik, raise savings rate before expanding lifestyle. Save percentage, bukan absolute amount.\n\nFinancial security starts with consistent saving.",
  investasi: "Investing merupakan wealth-building tool yang memanfaatkan compound interest dan time. Start early, even small, dan let time do the heavy lifting:\n\n1. Understand risk-return tradeoff. Higher returns require accepting higher volatility. Match investments dengan time horizon dan risk tolerance.\n\n2. Diversification adalah protection. Jangan all-in satu asset. Spread across stocks, bonds, real estate, dan geographies untuk reduce risk.\n\n3. Low-cost index funds untuk beginners. Most active managers tidak consistently beat market. Index funds memberi diversification dengan fees rendah.\n\n4. Time in market beats timing market. Don't try predict highs dan lows. Consistent investing (DCA) menghasilkan better long-term results.\n\n5. Educate before you invest. Understand apa yang Anda beli. Jangan follow tips tanpa research. Financial literacy prevents costly mistakes.\n\nLet your money work while you sleep.",
  utang: "Debt management merupakan critical skill untuk financial freedom. Tidak semua debt bad, tapi uncontrolled debt merupakan wealth destroyer:\n\n1. Good debt vs bad debt. Debt untuk appreciating assets (education, property) berbeda dari consumer debt untuk depreciating items.\n\n2. Avalanche atau snowball method. Avalanche: bayar highest interest first untuk save money. Snowball: bayar smallest balance first untuk momentum. Pilih yang sesuai psychology Anda.\n\n3. Stop adding fuel. Freeze credit card spending saat paying off debt. Cash-only spending prevents further accumulation.\n\n4. Negotiate better terms. Contact creditors untuk lower interest rates atau payment plans. Many are willing to work dengan borrowers proaktif.\n\n5. Professional help when needed. Credit counselors bisa help consolidate dan create plan. Don't wait until overwhelming untuk seek help.\n\nDebt freedom is possible with discipline and strategy.",

  // Teknologi
  hp: "Smartphone merupakan tool powerful yang bisa productive atau destructive tergantung penggunaan. Digital wellness berkisar pada intentional use, bukan avoidance:\n\n1. Boundaries with notifications. Disable non-essential alerts. Your attention adalah resource terbatas, protect it fiercely.\n\n2. 20-20-20 rule untuk mata. Setiap 20 menit, lihat sesuatu 20 feet (6 meter) jauhnya selama 20 detik. Reduce digital eye strain.\n\n3. Grayscale mode. Colorful icons dan notifications adalah designed to addict. Grayscale mengurangi dopamine hit dan impulsive checking.\n\n4. Designated phone-free zones. Bedroom untuk sleep, dining table untuk connection, car untuk safety. Sacred spaces improve quality of life.\n\n5. Intentional checking, not habitual. Ask sebelum buka: 'What am I looking for?' Mindless scrolling adalah time thief.\n\nControl your phone, don't let it control you.",
  laptop: "Laptop merupakan productivity tool yang memerlukan maintenance dan security awareness. Treat dengan baik untuk longevity dan performance optimal:\n\n1. Regular maintenance. Bersihkan debu dari ventilasi, update OS dan software, dan scan malware periodically. Prevention cheaper than repair.\n\n2. Battery health. Avoid overcharging dan deep discharges. Unplug saat 80%, charge saat 20%. Heat adalah enemy of battery longevity.\n\n3. Backup strategy. 3-2-1 rule: 3 copies, 2 different media, 1 offsite. Cloud storage plus external drive adalah minimum. Data loss bisa catastrophic.\n\n4. Ergonomics matter. Eye level screen, external keyboard untuk extended use, dan proper sitting position prevent repetitive strain injuries.\n\n5. Security hygiene. Strong unique passwords, 2FA enabled, dan encryption untuk sensitive files. Physical security juga penting di public spaces.\n\nYour laptop is your digital workspace - protect it.",
  aplikasi: "App ecosystem Anda mempengaruhi mental clarity dan productivity. Curate dengan intentionality, bukan install every trending app:\n\n1. Audit regularly. Review apps setiap 3 bulan. Delete yang jarang dipakai. Unused apps consume storage dan potentially privacy data.\n\n2. Single-purpose principle. Satu app untuk satu function utama. All-in-one solutions sering bloated dan less effective.\n\n3. Notification minimalism. Default adalah off, turn on selectively untuk truly urgent. Batch checking lebih fokus daripada constant interruptions.\n\n4. Digital minimalism. Fewer apps dengan mastery lebih baik daripada banyak apps dengan superficial use. Depth over breadth.\n\n5. Privacy awareness. Review permission requests. If free app seems too good, you're likely the product. Protect your data.\n\nQuality apps serve you; bad apps exploit you.",

  // Rumah Tangga & Relasi
  hubungan: "Healthy relationships merupakan dynamic systems yang memerlukan nurturing, boundaries, dan mutual growth. Quality over quantity applies to human connections:\n\n1. Communication fundamentals. Listen untuk understand, bukan untuk respond. 'I' statements daripada blame. Regular check-ins prevent resentment buildup.\n\n2. Boundaries create intimacy. Clear limits bukan rejection, melainkan roadmap untuk respectful interaction. Know your non-negotiables.\n\n3. Accept imperfection. No one is flawless; healthy relationships accommodate growth dan occasional mistakes. Forgiveness adalah skill.\n\n4. Invest time consistently. Relationships decay without attention. Quality time, acts of service, dan words of affirmation membangun emotional bank account.\n\n5. Know when to walk away. Toxic relationships damage wellbeing. Sometimes the healthiest choice adalah ending, not fixing.\n\nGood relationships should feel like home, not a battlefield.",
  pacar: "Dating merupakan discovery phase untuk compatibility assessment. Maintain individuality sambil building connection. Healthy dating berkisar pada fun, bukan pressure:\n\n1. Keep your independence. Maintain friendships, hobbies, dan personal goals. Codependency bukan romance, itu fear of being alone.\n\n2. Observe actions, not words. Consistency dalam behavior lebih revealing daripada verbal promises. Watch patterns over time.\n\n3. Communicate needs early. Don't play guessing games. Direct conversation tentang expectations prevents future conflict.\n\n4. Red flags are warnings. Disrespect, controlling behavior, atau inconsistent values adalah signals untuk reassess, not excuses to make.\n\n5. Enjoy the journey. Dating seharusnya enjoyable, bukan anxiety-inducing. If it's constant stress, itu bukan right fit.\n\nThe right person won't make you question your worth.",
  nikah: "Marriage merupakan partnership legal, emotional, dan practical yang memerlukan preparation beyond romance. Compatibility in values lebih predictive daripada chemistry:\n\n1. Pre-marital conversations. Diskusikan finances, children, career goals, family boundaries, dan deal-breakers sebelum engagement. Prevention better than divorce.\n\n2. Shared vision. Alignment dalam life direction, values hierarchy, dan definition of success reduces future friction.\n\n3. Conflict resolution skills. Marriage includes disagreement. Ability navigate conflict dengan respect adalah survival skill.\n\n4. Financial transparency. Money adalah topik conflict teratas. Joint planning, shared goals, dan honest discussion prevent resentment.\n\n5. Continuous courtship. Jangan stop dating setelah menikah. Intentional quality time maintains connection amid life's demands.\n\nLove is the beginning; commitment is the continuation.",
  keluarga: "Family dynamics shape kita profoundly, tapi juga bisa dibangun intentionally. Nuclear atau extended, healthy families merupakan safe havens:\n\n1. Quality over quantity time. Rituals seperti family meals, weekend activities, atau annual trips create shared memories dan identity.\n\n2. Open communication culture. Safe space untuk express feelings without judgment. 'Us versus the problem' daripada individual blame.\n\n3. Respect individual differences. Tiap member punya personality, dreams, dan boundaries. Acceptance lebih baik daripada forced conformity.\n\n4. Support without enabling. Help dalam crisis, tapi allow consequences untuk choices. Empowerment lebih baik daripada dependency.\n\n5. Navigate conflict gracefully. Disagreements normal. Repair attempts, apologies, dan forgiveness maintain family bonds.\n\nFamily is where life begins and love never ends.",
  orangtua: "Parenting merupakan leadership role terpenting yang tidak ada manual pasti. Adapt approach untuk child's unique temperament sambil providing consistent love dan boundaries:\n\n1. Connection before correction. Emotional bonding adalah foundation untuk influence. Children learn dari yang mereka feel connected to.\n\n2. Authoritative style works best. Warmth plus structure. High expectations dengan high support. Neither authoritarian (cold control) nor permissive (no boundaries).\n\n3. Model, don't just preach. Children mimic behavior, not words. Show empathy, resilience, dan integrity dalam daily life.\n\n4. Mistakes are learning opportunities. Don't fear letting children fail. Natural consequences teach lebih powerful daripada lectures.\n\n5. Self-care isn't selfish. Burnout parents can't parent well. Maintain your wellbeing untuk sustainably care for others.\n\nParenting is raising adults, not just managing children.",
  anak: "Child development berkisar pada nurturing potential, not molding clones. Each child merupakan individual dengan unique strengths, pace, dan path:\n\n1. Play is work for children. Unstructured play builds creativity, problem-solving, dan social skills. Don't overschedule dengan academics alone.\n\n2. Encourage growth mindset. Praise effort dan strategies, bukan innate ability. 'You worked hard' lebih baik daripada 'you're smart'.\n\n3. Emotional literacy. Teach naming emotions, healthy expression, dan coping strategies. EQ predicts success lebih dari IQ.\n\n4. Autonomy appropriate to age. Let them choose, decide, dan experience consequences. Independence builds confidence dan competence.\n\n5. Unconditional acceptance. Love isn't earned through achievement. Support their interests tanpa forcing your unfulfilled dreams.\n\nEvery child is a different kind of flower.",
  saudara: "Sibling relationships merupakan longest-lasting bonds dalam life. From childhood rivals ke adult allies, require intentional maintenance:\n\n1. Leave childhood roles behind. Don't treat adult siblings seperti you did at 10. Respect their growth dan current identity.\n\n2. Celebrate differences. Divergent paths, personalities, dan choices enrich family. Comparison breeds resentment.\n\n3. Support without judgment. Be there dalam crisis tanpa 'I told you so'. Unconditional support strengthens bonds.\n\n4. Create new memories. Adult rituals - trips, dinners, projects - maintain connection beyond shared past.\n\n5. Navigate inheritance carefully. Money conflicts can destroy families. Clear communication dan fairness prevent lifelong rifts.\n\nSiblings: your first friends and forever allies.",
  tetangga: "Neighbor relationships affect daily quality of life dan community safety. Balance friendliness dengan boundaries untuk harmonious coexistence:\n\n1. First impression matters. Introduce yourself early. Small gestures seperti smile atau brief chat membangun goodwill.\n\n2. Respect boundaries. Don't over-familiarize. Observe noise hours, property lines, dan privacy expectations.\n\n3. Be reliably helpful. Collect packages saat away, watch during vacation, atau bantu emergency. Reciprocity builds community.\n\n4. Address issues directly. Jika ada problem (noise, pets), discuss calmly dan privately sebelum escalate ke authorities.\n\n5. Participate selectively. Community events enhance belonging, tapi don't overcommit. Choose activities yang meaningful.\n\nGood neighbors make good neighborhoods.",
  teman: "Friendship merupakan voluntary relationship yang enrich life dan provide support system. Quality friendships require intentional cultivation dan mutual investment:\n\n1. Quality over quantity. Few deep friendships lebih fulfilling daripada banyak superficial connections. Invest dalam relationships yang reciprocal.\n\n2. Be present, not just available. Show up dalam celebrations dan crisis alike. Physical presence atau thoughtful reach-out demonstrates care.\n\n3. Vulnerability builds bonds. Share authentically, not just highlights. Being real about struggles creates intimacy dan trust.\n\n4. Respect their season. Friends have different capacity di different life stages. Don't take temporary distance personally.\n\n5. Reciprocity matters. One-sided friendships are exhausting. Healthy ones involve give dan take, support dan being supported.\n\nGood friends are the family you choose.",

  // Pengembangan Diri
  motivasi: "Tetap termotivasi memang tidak selalu mudah, terutama saat menghadapi tantangan atau rasa lelah. Berikut beberapa cara efektif untuk menjaga motivasi:\n\n1. Tetapkan tujuan yang jelas dan pecah menjadi langkah kecil. Milestone yang achievable membuat Anda merasa progress.\n\n2. Ingat 'why' Anda - alasan kuat di balik tujuan tersebut. Reconnect dengan purpose bisa menyalakan kembali semangat.\n\n3. Kelilingi diri dengan support system positif. Teman, keluarga, atau mentor yang supportive bisa menjadi fuel motivasi.\n\n4. Rayakan small wins. Setiap pencapaian, sekecil apa pun, layak diapresiasi sebagai bukti kemajuan.\n\n5. Self-care adalah investasi, bukan pengkhianatan. Istirahat yang cukup justru membuat Anda lebih produktif dan fokus.\n\n6. Visualisasikan kesuksesan. Bayangkan diri Anda telah mencapai tujuan - feeling itu bisa mendorong action.\n\n7. Belajar dari kegagalan sebagai stepping stone, bukan dead end. Setiap orang sukses punya koleksi kegagalan di belakangnya.\n\nIngat, motivasi bukan sesuatu yang selalu ada 100%. Ada hari where you just need to show up dan lakukan yang terbaik meski tidak sempurna. Consistency beats intensity.",
  target: "Goal setting berfungsi sebagai blueprint untuk intentional living. Effective goals motivate action dan provide direction tanpa overwhelming:\n\n1. SMART framework works. Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, Time-bound. Vague wishes menjadi actionable plans.\n\n2. Process over outcome goals. 'Write 500 words daily' lebih controllable daripada 'Write bestseller'. Focus on behaviors, not just results.\n\n3. Break down big goals. Milestones yang achievable create momentum. Large goals intimidate; small wins motivate.\n\n4. Review dan adjust regularly. Quarterly goal reviews keep you on track. Pivot jika circumstances change atau goals no longer serve you.\n\n5. Celebrate progress, not just completion. Acknowledge effort dan improvement. The journey matters as much as destination.\n\nGoals give direction; systems create results.",
  sukses: "Success merupakan self-defined concept, bukan society-imposed metric. Redefine untuk alignment dengan your values dan authentic desires:\n\n1. Define your own metrics. External validation (money, status) sering hollow tanpa alignment dengan personal values. What's meaningful untuk Anda?\n\n2. Process and progress matter. Success bukan hanya endpoint, melainkan growth, learning, dan who you become along the way.\n\n3. Sustainable over spectacular. Consistent small wins compound lebih baik daripada burnout chasing overnight success.\n\n4. Multidimensional success. Career, relationships, health, personal growth - balance across domains lebih fulfilling daripada single-domain obsession.\n\n5. Redefine failure. Setbacks adalah data, bukan definitions. Resilience dan adaptability are success skills.\n\nSuccess is living according to your values.",
  bahagia: "Happiness merupakan byproduct dari intentional living, bukan pursuit utama. Sustainable wellbeing comes dari habits dan mindset, not external circumstances:\n\n1. Practice gratitude daily. Three good things atau journaling shifts focus dari scarcity ke abundance. Brain adapts to what you notice.\n\n2. Invest dalam relationships. Strong social connections adalah strongest predictor of happiness. Quality time dengan loved ones beats material acquisitions.\n\n3. Align actions dengan values. Living authentically reduces cognitive dissonance. Know your values dan make decisions accordingly.\n\n4. Mindfulness dan presence. Future anxiety dan past rumination steal present joy. Savoring positive experiences deepens them.\n\n5. Contribution dan purpose. Helping others dan feeling useful creates meaning. Hedonic pleasures fade; purpose persists.\n\nHappiness is a skill, not a destination.",
  percaya: "Self-confidence merupakan trust dalam own abilities dan judgment. Built through experience, not affirmation. Competence creates confidence:\n\n1. Start small, build evidence. Small wins create confidence snowball. Each success proves you can, each failure teaches you how.\n\n2. Separate self dari performance. Failure dalam task bukan failure sebagai person. Self-worth tidak conditional pada achievement.\n\n3. Preparation reduces anxiety. Confidence often comes dari preparation. Practice, research, dan rehearsal make you ready.\n\n4. Body language matters. Posture, eye contact, dan speech pace affect internal state. Act confident untuk feel confident.\n\n5. Surround yourself dengan supporters. Limit exposure ke chronic critics. Build network yang believes in you dan your potential.\n\nConfidence is built through action, not waiting.",
  introvert: "Introversion merupakan temperament, bukan deficiency. Deep processing, meaningful connection preference, dan need untuk solitude merupakan strengths, bukan limitations:\n\n1. Understand your energy. Social interactions consume energy; solitude restores it. Plan recovery time setelah social events.\n\n2. Leverage deep thinking. Introverts excel dalam analysis, creativity, dan problem-solving. These are valuable skills dalam complex world.\n\n3. Quality relationships strategy. Few intimate friendships lebih fulfilling daripada large network. Depth over breadth dalam connections.\n\n4. Communication preferences. Writing often lebih comfortable daripada speaking. Use written communication untuk important messages.\n\n5. Set boundaries without guilt. Declining social invitations bukan rude, itu self-preservation. 'No' adalah complete sentence.\n\nIntroversion is a superpower when embraced.",

  // Spiritual & Filosofis
  agama: "Faith dan spirituality merupakan personal journeys yang provide meaning, community, dan moral framework. Respect untuk diverse beliefs sambil deepening your own path:\n\n1. Authenticity over performance. Religious practice untuk personal growth, bukan social signaling atau external validation.\n\n2. Question dan explore. Faith yang kuat bisa withstand doubt dan inquiry. Understanding deepens belief, blind obedience doesn't.\n\n3. Practice core values. Compassion, justice, humility - universal principles across traditions. Behavior matters more than ritual.\n\n4. Interfaith respect. Different paths bisa lead ke similar values. Learn dari others tanpa compromising your own beliefs.\n\n5. Community dan solitude balance. Religious community provides support; personal contemplation provides clarity. Both necessary.\n\nSpirituality is between you and your understanding of the divine.",
  makna: "Meaning in life merupakan subjective construct, not universal given. Purpose discovered through exploration, suffering, contribution, dan reflection:\n\n1. Service kepada others. Helping people dalam need creates visceral sense of purpose. Altruism connects us ke something larger.\n\n2. Mastery dan creation. Developing skills dan creating something - art, business, relationships - provides deep satisfaction.\n\n3. Relationships sebagai anchor. Love dan connection adalah fundamental human needs. Being there untuk others gives life significance.\n\n4. Transcendence experiences. Nature, art, meditation, atau religious moments where self-boundaries dissolve. Peak experiences remind us of wonder.\n\n5. Values-based living. Acting sesuai principles yang matter, even dalam difficulty. Integrity creates internal coherence.\n\nMeaning is found in the living, not the answers.",
  mati: "Death awareness, rather than morbid, bisa menjadi powerful catalyst untuk authentic living. Memento mori: remember you will die, therefore live fully:\n\n1. Mortality membuat life precious. Finite time creates urgency dan meaning. Immortality would make moments less valuable.\n\n2. Legacy thinking. What endures after you? Relationships influenced, values passed on, atau work yang continues helping others.\n\n3. Present moment focus. Death adalah future certainty; life adalah present possibility. Don't postpone living.\n\n4. Preparation reduces anxiety. Practical matters: wills, healthcare directives, conversations dengan loved ones. Control what you can.\n\n5. Grief is love's price. Loss hurts karena connections matter. Honor grief sebagai testament to love, not weakness.\n\nDeath is certain; how we live is choice.",

  // Lainnya
  cuaca: "Weather affects mood, energy, dan productivity through biological mechanisms. Adapt rather than fight untuk maintain wellbeing:\n\n1. Light exposure management. Gray days: maximize natural light, consider light therapy. Sunny days: enjoy outdoor benefits, protect skin.\n\n2. Seasonal adjustment. Don't expect summer productivity dalam winter. Adjust expectations dan schedules untuk seasonal rhythms.\n\n3. Preparation prevents discomfort. Check forecast, dress appropriately, keep emergency supplies. Weather surprises shouldn't be dangerous.\n\n4. Find enjoyment dalam extremes. Rainy days untuk reading; snow untuk beauty; heat untuk swimming. Each weather offers something.\n\n5. Climate adaptation. Long-term residents adapt homes, routines, dan clothing untuk local climate. Work with, not against, environment.\n\nWeather is reality; our response is choice.",
  bencana: "Disaster preparedness merupakan responsibility dan self-care. Panic kills more than disasters; preparation saves lives:\n\n1. Emergency plan siap sedia. Know evacuation routes, meeting points, dan communication protocols. Practice drills dengan family.\n\n2. 72-hour kit essentials. Air, food, medications, documents, cash, flashlight, first aid. Self-sufficiency until help arrives.\n\n3. Information dari sumber resmi. Follow official channels untuk accurate updates. Misinformation spreads fast dalam crises.\n\n4. Community resilience. Know neighbors, support vulnerable, share resources. Collective preparedness lebih effective daripada individual.\n\n5. Mental preparedness. Accept that disasters happen. Psychological resilience helps make better decisions under pressure.\n\nHope for the best, prepare for the worst.",
  politis: "Political engagement merupakan civic responsibility yang memerlukan critical thinking dan sustained attention. Democracy requires informed citizens:\n\n1. Multiple sources verification. Cross-check information across diverse media. Algorithm bubbles create distorted reality.\n\n2. Policy over personality. Evaluate platforms, track records, dan impacts rather than charisma atau slogans.\n\n3. Local matters enormously. National politics gets attention; local decisions affect daily life directly. Engage in community governance.\n\n4. Civil discourse. Disagreement adalah normal; dehumanization is destructive. Argue ideas, respect people.\n\n5. Consistent participation. Voting adalah minimum; ongoing advocacy, volunteering, dan holding representatives accountable adalah citizenship.\n\nDemocracy is not a spectator sport.",
  transport: "Transportation choices affect productivity, budget, environment, dan wellbeing. Intentional mobility planning saves time dan reduces stress:\n\n1. Plan routes strategically. Check traffic, transit schedules, atau flight options beforehand. Unexpected delays ruin punctuality.\n\n2. Buffer time adalah essential. Depart earlier than calculated necessary. Late arrival anxiety is avoidable dengan preparation.\n\n3. Multi-modal options. Combine walking, biking, public transit, dan driving untuk optimal efficiency. Different modes suit different journeys.\n\n4. Sustainable choices. Public transit, carpooling, atau active transport reduce carbon footprint dan often save money.\n\n5. Safety non-negotiable. Seatbelts, helmets, situational awareness. Arriving late is better than not arriving at all.\n\nMovement is freedom; plan it wisely.",
  liburan: "Travel and breaks merupakan essential untuk mental reset dan perspective expansion. Balance planning dengan openness untuk unexpected joy:\n\n1. Purpose defines planning. Adventure, relaxation, atau cultural exploration? Different goals require different preparation.\n\n2. Research essentials, wing the rest. Book key logistics; leave room untuk spontaneous discoveries. Over-planning kills serendipity.\n\n3. Disconnect untuk reconnect. Limit work communication. Presence enhances experience dan actual restoration.\n\n4. Document mindfully. Capture memories tanpa experiencing everything through lens. Balance photography dengan direct experience.\n\n5. Return buffer. Schedule recovery day sebelum work resumes. Post-vacation crash is real; plan untuk it.\n\nTravel far enough to meet yourself.",
  kado: "Gift-giving merupakan love language dan social bond. Thoughtfulness matters more than price; understanding recipient is the art:\n\n1. Listen untuk clues. Throughout year, people mention things they want atau need. Great gift-givers are great listeners.\n\n2. Experiences over objects. Memories last; clutter doesn't. Concert tickets, workshops, atau trips often lebih appreciated than things.\n\n3. Presentation matters. Thoughtful wrapping, personal note, atau creative delivery enhances emotional impact.\n\n4. It's okay to ask. Direct questions atau gift registries reduce guesswork. Better wanted gift than unwanted surprise.\n\n5. Presence as present. Sometimes quality time together adalah gift yang paling berharga. Attention adalah scarce commodity.\n\nThe best gifts come from paying attention.",

  // Topik Umum Tambahan
  waktu: "Time merupakan non-renewable resource. Management is really self-management; how you allocate attention determines life quality:\n\n1. Audit your time. Track actual usage selama seminggu. Often shocking gap antara perceived dan actual time allocation.\n\n2. Eisenhower matrix. Urgent vs important quadrants. Focus on important-not-urgent untuk strategic progress, not just firefighting.\n\n3. Time-blocking works. Schedule specific blocks untuk specific tasks. Intentionality prevents drift dan distractions.\n\n4. Single-tasking wins. Multitasking adalah rapid task-switching yang reduces quality dan increases errors. Focus deeply.\n\n5. Protect downtime. Rest, play, dan unstructured time adalah productive untuk creativity dan wellbeing. All work is unsustainable.\n\nTime is what we want most but use worst.",
  skill: "Skill acquisition follows learning curves yang bisa dipercepat dengan right methodology. Quality of practice matters more than quantity:\n\n1. Deliberate practice, not just repetition. Push beyond comfort zone, target weaknesses, get immediate feedback. Mindless repetition doesn't improve.\n\n2. Deconstruct complex skills. Break down into sub-skills; master components before whole. Chunking accelerates learning.\n\n3. Immediate feedback loops. Know what you did wrong right away. Delayed feedback allows reinforcement of errors.\n\n4. Mental rehearsal works. Visualize execution; brain processes similarly to actual practice. Supplement physical practice.\n\n5. Teach to learn deeper. Explaining concepts atau demonstrating skills exposes gaps dan solidifies understanding.\n\nSkills compound; start building early.",
  komunikasi: "Communication merupakan fundamental life skill yang affects every relationship dan outcome. It's transmission, reception, dan interpretation:\n\n1. Listen untuk understand. Most listen untuk respond. Active listening: paraphrase, ask questions, suspend judgment.\n\n2. Clarity over cleverness. Simple language, structure messages, get to point. Confusion adalah enemy of effectiveness.\n\n3. Non-verbal alignment. Body language, tone, dan words should match. Mixed signals create distrust.\n\n4. Adapt untuk audience. Technical depth untuk experts; simplicity untuk laypeople. Context determines approach.\n\n5. Empathy as foundation. Understand others' perspectives before responding. Connection precedes persuasion.\n\nCommunication is the response you get.",
  networking: "Professional relationships merupakan career multiplier. Authentic networking merupakan mutual value exchange, bukan transactional collecting:\n\n1. Give before asking. Offer help, introductions, atau insights first. Reciprocity naturally follows generosity.\n\n2. Quality over quantity. Deep relationships dengan key people lebih valuable daripada shallow connections dengan many.\n\n3. Follow-up dengan value. Reference previous conversation, share relevant article, atau offer specific assistance. Memorable beats generic.\n\n4. Maintain weak ties. Acquaintances often provide opportunities more than close friends due to different circles.\n\n5. Online presence strategic. LinkedIn profile yang complete, thoughtful content, dan genuine engagement build reputation.\n\nYour network is your net worth.",
  presentasi: "Presentation merupakan influence skill yang combines content, structure, dan delivery. Audience engagement lebih penting daripada information dump:\n\n1. Know your audience. Their needs, knowledge level, dan concerns shape content. Relevance determines attention.\n\n2. Structure dengan clarity. Opening hook, clear agenda, 3-5 key points, memorable close. Confusing structure loses audience.\n\n3. Visual aids support, don't lead. Minimal text, maximum visual. You are presenter; slides are backup.\n\n4. Rehearse extensively. Practice out loud, with timer, dalam front of mirror. Familiarity creates confidence.\n\n5. Handle Q&A gracefully. Listen fully, repeat question, answer concisely. 'I don't know, I'll find out' adalah acceptable.\n\nPresentation is about connection, not perfection.",
  memasak: "Cooking merupakan life skill dan creative outlet yang nourish body dan relationships. Mastery comes dari repetition, curiosity, dan willingness to fail:\n\n1. Master fundamentals first. Knife skills, heat control, seasoning. Basics yang solid make everything easier.\n\n2. Taste as you go. Adjust seasoning progressively. Palate development makes you better cook over time.\n\n3. Quality ingredients matter. Fresh produce, good oils, proper seasoning elevate simple dishes.\n\n4. Don't fear experimentation. Recipes are guidelines, not gospel. Adapt berdasarkan preference dan available ingredients.\n\n5. Cooking as connection. Meals shared dengan others create memories. Hospitality strengthens relationships.\n\nCooking is love made visible.",
  kopi: "Coffee appreciation merupakan sensory journey dari bean to cup. Quality extraction memerlukan attention to variables yang affect flavor:\n\n1. Fresh beans are essential. Roast date matters; coffee stale within weeks. Grind just before brewing untuk preserve aromatics.\n\n2. Grind size determines extraction. Too coarse = underextracted (sour); too fine = overextracted (bitter). Match grind to method.\n\n3. Water temperature critical. 90-96°C optimal. Boiling water scorches; too cool underextracts.\n\n4. Ratio dan timing. Standard 1:15 (coffee:water) sebagai starting point. Adjust untuk strength preference.\n\n5. Explore brewing methods. V60, French press, espresso, cold brew - each offers unique flavor profile. Variety prevents boredom.\n\nCoffee is a ritual, not just caffeine.",
  membaca: "Reading merupakan cognitive workout dan empathy training yang meningkatkan knowledge, focus, dan perspective. Quality over quantity dalam book consumption:\n\n1. Read actively, not passively. Highlight, annotate, summarize. Engage dengan ideas untuk deeper retention.\n\n2. Mix genres strategically. Fiction builds empathy; non-fiction builds knowledge; poetry builds language appreciation.\n\n3. Abandon bad books. Life is too short untuk finish books yang don't serve you. Sunk cost fallacy applies to reading too.\n\n4. Create reading rituals. Dedicated time, comfortable space, minimal distractions. Environment shapes habits.\n\n5. Discuss what you read. Book clubs, summaries, atau conversations solidify understanding dan expose blind spots.\n\nReading is to the mind what exercise is to the body.",
  menulis: "Writing merupakan thinking tool dan communication skill yang sharpens dengan practice. Clear writing reflects clear thinking:\n\n1. Daily practice builds fluency. Morning pages, journaling, atau short pieces. Consistency matters more than length.\n\n2. Clarity over cleverness. Simple sentences, logical flow, specific examples. If confused, reader is confused.\n\n3. Read your work aloud. Awkward phrasing, repetition, dan unclear logic become obvious when spoken.\n\n4. Feedback improves quality. Trusted readers catch what you miss. Revision adalah where good writing becomes great.\n\n5. Imitate then innovate. Study writers you admire. Analyze their techniques, then develop your own voice.\n\nWrite to think, think to write.",
  musik: "Music merupakan universal language yang affects emotion, cognition, dan physical state. Engage actively, not just passively consume:\n\n1. Active listening practice. Focus on instruments, structure, lyrics. Concert or quality headphones enhance experience.\n\n2. Learn an instrument. Even basic proficiency changes how you hear music. Motor and cognitive benefits are significant.\n\n3. Genre exploration. Don't stay dalam comfort zone. Classical, jazz, world music - each offers unique structures dan emotions.\n\n4. Functional playlists. Match music to activity: upbeat untuk workout, calm untuk focus, nostalgic untuk comfort.\n\n5. Live music experiences. Concerts, local gigs, atau playing dengan others. Community around music enriches appreciation.\n\nMusic is the soundtrack of life.",
  film: "Cinema merupakan art form combining visual storytelling, performance, sound, dan editing. Watch dengan critical eye untuk deeper appreciation:\n\n1. Beyond entertainment. Analyze cinematography, editing, sound design, acting choices. Technical appreciation enhances enjoyment.\n\n2. Genre conventions. Understand what different genres promise dan deliver. Horror, comedy, drama - each has unique tools.\n\n3. Cultural context matters. Films reflect their era, culture, dan constraints. Historical context deepens understanding.\n\n4. Director as auteur. Follow specific directors' evolution. Their obsessions, visual signatures, dan thematic concerns.\n\n5. Discuss dan dissect. Reviews, conversations, atau essays clarify interpretation. Multiple perspectives enrich experience.\n\nFilm is truth 24 times per second.",
  fotografi: "Photography merupakan technical skill dan artistic vision yang capture moments and create visual narratives. Master equipment kemudian forget it:\n\n1. Light is everything. Golden hour, blue hour, soft window light - quality of light matters more than expensive gear.\n\n2. Composition fundamentals. Rule of thirds, leading lines, framing, negative space. Guidelines, not rules.\n\n3. Exposure triangle mastery. ISO, aperture, shutter speed work together. Understand trade-offs untuk intentional results.\n\n4. Moment over perfection. Candid emotion beats technical perfection. Anticipate dan capture decisive moments.\n\n5. Edit dengan restraint. Post-processing enhances, tidak menggantikan good capture. Subtle adjustments beat heavy filters.\n\nThe best camera is the one you have with you.",
  traveling: "Travel merupakan education through experience yang expands worldview dan builds adaptability. Approach dengan openness dan respect:\n\n1. Research enables respect. Understand basic customs, taboos, dan history. Ignorance breeds insensitivity.\n\n2. Local immersion over tourism. Neighborhood walks, local transport, authentic cuisine. Go beyond tourist bubble.\n\n3. Learning some language. Even basic phrases show respect dan open doors. Locals appreciate effort, not perfection.\n\n4. Document reflectively. Photos plus journaling preserve context dan feelings. Memories fade; records remain.\n\n5. Flexibility with plans. Missed trains, closed attractions, unexpected detours often become best stories.\n\nTravel is the only thing you buy that makes you richer.",
  hewan: "Pet companionship offers unconditional love dan teaches responsibility. Proper care requires research, resources, dan lifetime commitment:\n\n1. Species-specific needs. Research thoroughly sebelum commit. Diet, exercise, space, social needs vary dramatically.\n\n2. Financial preparedness. Food, vet care, emergencies. Pets are expensive; plan for costs over lifetime, not just adoption.\n\n3. Time investment daily. Exercise, grooming, attention. Neglect causes behavioral problems dan suffering.\n\n4. Training dengan patience. Positive reinforcement works; punishment damages trust. Consistency dan kindness build bond.\n\n5. Adoption over shopping. Shelters have amazing animals needing homes. Save lives rather than supporting unethical breeding.\n\nPets are family, not possessions.",
  tanaman: "Gardening merupakan meditation dan science yang connect you ke natural cycles. Patience dan observation lead to green thumb:\n\n1. Match plants to conditions. Light, humidity, space constraints. Right plant in right place thrives; wrong plant struggles.\n\n2. Water wisely. Overwatering kills more than underwatering. Check soil moisture; most plants prefer dry spells between watering.\n\n3. Soil health matters. Quality potting mix, appropriate drainage, occasional fertilizing. Roots need healthy environment.\n\n4. Observation is key. Plants communicate through leaves, growth patterns. Learn read their signals untuk proper care.\n\n5. Enjoy the process. Growth takes time. Tending, waiting, celebrating new leaves - gardening teaches patience dan presence.\n\nGardening is cheaper than therapy.",
  minimalis: "Minimalism berkisar pada intentionality, bukan deprivation. Curate possessions, commitments, dan digital life untuk focus pada what truly matters:\n\n1. Start dengan categories, not rooms. Clothes, books, documents - complete one category before next. KonMari method works.\n\n2. Keep what adds value. Question: Does this support my goals? Spark joy? Serve practical purpose? If not, let go.\n\n3. Quality over quantity. One excellent item beats many mediocre. Invest dalam things yang last dan serve well.\n\n4. Digital minimalism too. Unsubscribe, unfollow, delete apps. Information diet is as important as physical declutter.\n\n5. Mindset shift. Stop comparing, stop consuming reactively. Experiences dan relationships over accumulation.\n\nLess stuff, more life.",
  lingkungan: "Environmental responsibility merupakan collective action issue. Individual choices matter, tapi systemic change juga necessary:\n\n1. Reduce comes first. Less consumption beats better consumption. Refuse what you don't need sebelum thinking about recycling.\n\n2. Vote dengan wallet. Support companies dengan sustainable practices. Consumer demand drives corporate behavior.\n\n3. Energy efficiency. Simple habits: unplug devices, efficient appliances, reduce heating/cooling. Cumulative impact significant.\n\n4. Transportation choices. Walk, bike, transit, or electric vehicles. Transportation adalah major emission source.\n\n5. Advocate dan educate. Beyond personal action, support policy changes dan educate others. Collective impact multiplies.\n\nWe don't inherit the earth from our ancestors; we borrow it from our children.",
  volunteer: "Volunteering merupakan win-win: help community dan personal growth. Meaningful contribution connects you ke something larger:\n\n1. Align dengan values. Choose causes yang genuinely resonate. Passion sustains commitment lebih dari obligation.\n\n2. Start small, grow organically. Don't overcommit initially. Test fit dengan small role before taking leadership.\n\n3. Use your skills. Pro bono professional work often lebih valuable daripada unskilled labor. Leverage expertise.\n\n4. Consistency beats intensity. Regular small contributions lebih impactful daripada sporadic big efforts.\n\n5. Reflect on impact. Document experiences, growth, dan connections gained. Volunteering transforms giver juga.\n\nService is the rent we pay for living.",
  hobby: "Hobbies merupakan essential untuk wellbeing, creativity, dan identity beyond work. Pursue untuk joy, bukan productivity:\n\n1. Process over outcome. Create tanpa judgment. Hobbies are for enjoyment, not performance atau monetization.\n\n2. Diverse interests. Physical, creative, intellectual - different types balance each other. Variety prevents burnout.\n\n3. Schedule protected time. Calendar your hobbies seperti important meetings. Non-negotiable restoration time.\n\n4. Community aspect. Join clubs, classes, atau online groups. Shared passion creates meaningful connections.\n\n5. Beginner's mind. Stay curious, embrace mistakes, enjoy learning. Hobbies are where perfectionism should die.\n\nA hobby a day keeps the burnout away.",
  keamanan: "Digital security merupakan hygiene, bukan one-time setup. Threats evolve; defenses must adapt. Protect yourself dan others:\n\n1. Password discipline. Unique per account, password manager, enable 2FA everywhere. Credential stuffing adalah common attack.\n\n2. Phishing awareness. Verify sender, check URLs, don't click suspicious links. Social engineering is primary attack vector.\n\n3. Update promptly. Security patches fix known vulnerabilities. Delayed updates are exploitable windows.\n\n4. Backup strategy. Ransomware exists; backups are insurance. 3-2-1 rule untuk critical data.\n\n5. Privacy settings. Review regularly, limit data exposure, understand what you're sharing. Default settings often too permissive.\n\nSecurity is not a product, but a process.",

  // Teknologi & Digital Tambahan
  ai: "AI merupakan augmentation tool, bukan replacement untuk human judgment. Leverage capabilities wisely while maintaining critical thinking:\n\n1. Know the limitations. AI confidently wrong sometimes. Verify facts, especially untuk important decisions.\n\n2. Use untuk ideation. Brainstorming, first drafts, exploring angles. Starting point, bukan final product.\n\n3. Enhance productivity. Automate repetitive tasks, summarize long documents, translate. Focus human effort pada high-value work.\n\n4. Ethical considerations. Bias dalam training data, environmental cost, labor issues. Use responsibly.\n\n5. Human-in-the-loop. Important decisions require human judgment. AI informs; humans decide.\n\nAI is a tool; you are the craftsman.",
  coding: "Belajar coding dari nol memang menantang tapi sangat memungkinkan. Berikut roadmap efektif untuk pemula:\n\n1. Pilih satu bahasa pemrograman (Python untuk AI/data, JavaScript untuk web, atau Java untuk enterprise). Jangan belajar banyak bahasa sekaligus - fokus dulu satu sampai confident.\n\n2. Kuasai fundamentals: variable, data types, control flow, function, dan object-oriented. Dasar yang kuat akan memudahkan belajar bahasa lain nanti.\n\n3. Practice over theory. Untuk setiap konsep yang dipelajari, langsung tulis kode. Gunakan platform seperti LeetCode (algoritma), freeCodeCamp (project-based), atau Codecademy (interactive).\n\n4. Buat proyek kecil yang personally meaningful. Kalau suka film, buat movie tracker. Suka masak, buat recipe app. Motivasi lebih tinggi kalau membuat sesuatu yang Anda gunakan sendiri.\n\n5. Gabung komunitas: Discord server programming, local meetup, atau forum. Belajar bareng membuat journey lebih enjoyable dan dapat mentorship.\n\n6. Debugging adalah skill, bukan keberuntungan. Saat stuck, trace error message, Google spesifik, dan jangan takut bertanya di Stack Overflow dengan format yang jelas.\n\n7. Consistency beats intensity. 30 menit setiap hari lebih efektif dari 5 jam sekali seminggu. Build habit coding di jam yang sama setiap hari.\n\nRemember: Every expert was once a beginner. Jangan bandingkan diri dengan programmer senior yang sudah 10 tahun berpengalaman.",
  website: "Web presence merupakan digital real estate. Build sesuai needs: quick landing page atau custom platform. Right tool untuk right job:\n\n1. Define purpose first. Portfolio, blog, e-commerce, atau web app? Different goals require different approaches.\n\n2. No-code untuk speed. WordPress, Webflow, atau Wix untuk quick deployment without coding. Focus on content dan business.\n\n3. Code untuk control. HTML/CSS/JS atau frameworks (React, Vue) untuk full customization. Learning curve exists tapi flexibility tinggi.\n\n4. UX over aesthetics. Navigation, load speed, mobile responsiveness matter more than visual polish. Function first.\n\n5. Content is king. Great design dengan poor content fails. Invest dalam writing, photography, dan value proposition.\n\nYour website is your 24/7 ambassador.",
  data: "Data literacy merupakan critical skill di modern economy. Ability to interpret, analyze, dan visualize data informs better decisions:\n\n1. Start dengan spreadsheets. Excel/Google Sheets fundamentals: formulas, pivot tables, charts. Foundation untuk semua analysis.\n\n2. SQL untuk data extraction. Query databases untuk specific information. Most companies store data dalam relational databases.\n\n3. Python untuk advanced analysis. Pandas library untuk manipulation, matplotlib untuk visualization. Coding scales your capability.\n\n4. Critical interpretation. Correlation isn't causation. Question data sources, methodology, dan potential bias.\n\n5. Storytelling dengan data. Insights must be communicated clearly. Visualizations dan narratives drive action.\n\nData is the new oil, but literacy is the refinery.",

  // Keseharian & Praktis
  resep: "Recipe mastery merupakan combination of following instructions dan developing intuition. Start faithful, then personalize:\n\n1. Read completely before starting. Mise en place: prepare all ingredients beforehand. Chaos in kitchen ruins outcomes.\n\n2. Trust but verify. Recipe ratings dan reviews offer insights. Common modifications indicate flexibility points.\n\n3. Taste dan adjust. Palate varies; salt, acid, sweetness levels are personal. Recipes are starting points.\n\n4. Document successes. When you nail a dish, write down exactly what you did. Future replication requires records.\n\n5. Embrace failures. Burnt, oversalted, atau undercooked adalah learning data. Analyze what went wrong.\n\nRecipes are guides; your taste is the goal.",
  cuci: "Laundry merupakan maintenance skill yang extends clothing lifespan. Proper technique saves money dan keeps items looking good:\n\n1. Sort strategically. By color (lights/darks) dan fabric weight. Heavy fabrics damage delicate dalam same cycle.\n\n2. Read care labels. 'Dry clean only' means exactly that. Ignoring instructions ruins expensive items.\n\n3. Don't overdose detergent. More isn't cleaner; excess leaves residue. Measure carefully, use appropriate amount.\n\n4. Cold water default. Modern detergents work dalam cold. Saves energy, prevents shrinking dan color fading.\n\n5. Air dry when possible. Dryers cause wear dan shrinkage. Line drying preserves fabric integrity longer.\n\nClean clothes, careful process.",
  bersih: "Clean space affects mental clarity dan physical health. Systematic approach prevents overwhelm dan maintains order:\n\n1. Declutter dulu, clean later. Organized spaces are easier to clean. Reduce stuff reduces cleaning burden.\n\n2. Daily micro-cleaning. 10-15 minutes maintenance prevents marathon sessions. Wipe surfaces, put things away.\n\n3. Zone approach. Divide space into areas; complete one before moving on. Prevents partial progress everywhere.\n\n4. Right tools matter. Quality cleaning supplies make job faster dan more effective. Invest dalam basics.\n\n5. Schedule deep cleans. Monthly atau seasonal thorough cleaning. Calendar it seperti other appointments.\n\nClean space, clear mind.",
  dekor: "Decor creates environment yang influences mood dan productivity. Personal expression meets functionality:\n\n1. Define your aesthetic. Browse inspiration, identify patterns dalam what attracts you. Coherent vision guides choices.\n\n2. Budget-smart sourcing. Thrift stores, flea markets, estate sales offer unique pieces dengan character.\n\n3. Color harmony. Choose palette (3-4 colors) dan repeat throughout. Cohesion creates calm; chaos creates stress.\n\n4. Lighting transforms. Layer ambient, task, dan accent lighting. Most underrated aspect of room design.\n\n5. Personal touches matter. Photos, travel souvenirs, handmade items. Space should tell your story.\n\nDecorate for how you want to feel.",

  // Kesehatan Mental & Self-Care
  meditasi: "Meditation merupakan mental training yang reduces stress, improves focus, dan increases self-awareness. Regular practice changes brain structure:\n\n1. Start small, grow gradually. 5-10 minutes daily beats sporadic hour-long sessions. Consistency builds habit.\n\n2. Focus on breath. When mind wanders (it will), gently return attention to breathing. That's the practice.\n\n3. Guided apps help. Headspace, Calm, Insight Timer provide structure untuk beginners. Training wheels until independent.\n\n4. Non-judgmental awareness. Observe thoughts tanpa engagement. You're not your thoughts; you're the observer.\n\n5. Anywhere, anytime. Commute, waiting in line, before sleep. Mini-meditations throughout day accumulate benefits.\n\nMeditation is a practice, not a performance.",
  jurnal: "Journaling merupakan therapeutic tool untuk emotional processing, clarity, dan self-discovery. Private space untuk honest reflection:\n\n1. Morning pages. Stream-of-consciousness writing immediately upon waking. Clears mental clutter before day begins.\n\n2. Gratitude practice. 3 specific things daily. Shifts focus dari scarcity ke abundance. Details matter lebih than generic.\n\n3. Evening reflection. Review day: what worked, what didn't, what learned. Patterns emerge over time.\n\n4. Problem-solving. Write about challenges from third-person perspective. Distance creates objectivity.\n\n5. No rules, just write. Grammar, spelling, coherence don't matter. Honesty dan consistency do.\n\nPaper is more patient than people.",
  boundaries: "Healthy boundaries merupakan self-care essentials. Define where you end dan others begin, protecting your wellbeing:\n\n1. Know your limits. Physical, emotional, time, energy boundaries. Self-awareness precedes boundary-setting.\n\n2. 'No' is complete sentence. You don't owe explanations. Over-explaining invites negotiation.\n\n3. Communicate clearly. Vague boundaries confuse. State expectations dan consequences explicitly.\n\n4. Consistency reinforces. Enforce boundaries setiap kali violated. Inconsistency teaches boundaries are optional.\n\n5. Guilt is temporary; resentment is lasting. Short-term discomfort saying no beats long-term resentment dari yes.\n\nBoundaries are the distance at which I can love you and me simultaneously.",
  burnout: "Burnout merupakan occupational phenomenon dari chronic workplace stress. Not personal failing; systemic issue requiring intervention:\n\n1. Recognize warning signs. Cynicism, exhaustion, reduced efficacy. Early detection prevents collapse.\n\n2. Rest isn't enough. Recovery requires addressing root causes: workload, control, reward, community, fairness, values.\n\n3. Reconnect dengan purpose. Why did you choose this work? Rediscover meaning atau consider if values have changed.\n\n4. Negotiate changes. Boundaries, delegation, role adjustments. Sometimes only solution adalah leaving toxic environment.\n\n5. Professional help. Therapy, career coaching, atau medical intervention. Burnout can be severe; treat seriously.\n\nYou can't pour from an empty cup.",

  // Finansial Lanjut
  freelance: "Freelancing merupakan entrepreneurship dengan flexibility tapi juga uncertainty. Success requires business mindset, not just skills:\n\n1. Structure creates freedom. Set work hours, dedicated workspace, routines. Discipline replaces external accountability.\n\n2. Separate finances. Business account, track expenses, set aside taxes. Financial clarity prevents nasty surprises.\n\n3. Client management skills. Contracts, scope definition, communication. Under-promise dan over-deliver builds reputation.\n\n4. Pipeline always. Even when busy, market yourself. Feast-famine cycles are real; preparation prevents panic.\n\n5. Benefits self-funded. Healthcare, retirement, paid time off. Calculate true rate needed untuk cover these costs.\n\nYou're the CEO of your own career.",
  sidehustle: "Side hustles merupakan low-risk experimentation with entrepreneurship. Test ideas tanpa quitting day job:\n\n1. Validate before scaling. Market research, minimum viable product, pre-sales. Don't invest heavily before proof of demand.\n\n2. Use existing skills. Leverage what you already know. Learning new skill plus building business is overwhelming.\n\n3. Time management critical. Don't let side hustle compromise main income atau health. Boundaries protect both.\n\n4. Track metrics. Revenue, time invested, hourly rate. Ensure it's actually profitable, not just busy work.\n\n5. Pivot atau persevere. Objective assessment: growing atau stagnant? Sometimes walking away adalah right decision.\n\nSide hustles should add to life, not drain it.",
  pasif: "Passive income requires upfront investment creating assets yang generate ongoing returns. Not free money; delayed rewards:\n\n1. Digital products. E-books, courses, templates. Create once, sell repeatedly. Quality determines longevity.\n\n2. Content monetization. YouTube, blog, podcast dengan ads/sponsorships. Requires consistent content creation dulu.\n\n3. Affiliate marketing. Recommend products you genuinely use. Trust is currency; don't recommend garbage.\n\n4. Investment income. Dividend stocks, REITs, interest. Requires capital dulu; money makes money.\n\n5. Reality check. Truly passive is rare; most require maintenance. Evaluate effort-to-reward ratio honestly.\n\nPassive income is making money while you sleep, after working hard while awake.",
  pajak: "Tax literacy prevents overpayment dan legal issues. Understand obligations, deductions, dan optimization strategies:\n\n1. Know your obligations. Income thresholds, filing deadlines, payment schedules. Ignorance isn't defense.\n\n2. Document everything. Receipts, invoices, mileage logs. Deductions require proof; assumptions don't suffice.\n\n3. Professional guidance. Complex situations (business, investments, international) benefit dari expert advice.\n\n4. Plan strategically. Retirement contributions, timing income, legitimate deductions. Legal optimization isn't evasion.\n\n5. Software helps. Tax preparation software atau apps track throughout year, reducing April stress.\n\nThe only certainties are death and taxes.",

  // Relasi Sosial
  conflict: "Conflict merupakan inevitable dalam relationships. Managed well, it strengthens bonds; handled poorly, it destroys them:\n\n1. Focus on issue, not person. 'I feel frustrated when...' not 'You always...'. Behavior critique, not character attack.\n\n2. Seek understanding first. Paraphrase their view before responding. They need to feel heard before they can listen.\n\n3. Identify underlying needs. Positions are what people say they want; interests are why. Address interests untuk resolution.\n\n4. Multiple solutions exist. Win-win requires creativity. Brainstorm options before evaluating.\n\n5. Know when to pause. Heated moments produce poor decisions. 'Let's take 20 minutes' prevents escalation.\n\nConflict handled well is intimacy fertilizer.",
  toxic: "Toxic relationships drain more than they give. Recognizing signs early allows for informed decisions about boundaries atau exit:\n\n1. Recognize the signs. Consistent criticism, lack of reciprocity, gaslighting, emotional blackmail. Trust your gut feeling.\n\n2. Document patterns. Specific incidents over time. Clarity about reality when manipulation makes you doubt yourself.\n\n3. Set firm boundaries. State clearly what is unacceptable. Enforcement communicates seriousness.\n\n4. Limit engagement. Reduce contact, change communication patterns. You don't owe anyone unlimited access.\n\n5. Professional support. Therapy helps process gaslighting effects dan rebuild self-trust. Don't navigate alone.\n\nYou can't heal in the same environment that made you sick.",
  single: "Singlehood merupakan opportunity, not waiting room. Self-development saat single determines relationship quality later:\n\n1. Self-discovery priority. Values, preferences, life goals. Clarity about self attracts compatible partners.\n\n2. Build complete life. Career, friendships, hobbies, health. Don't seek partner to complete you; be complete already.\n\n3. Address attachment patterns. Therapy atau self-work untuk understand relationship tendencies. Awareness prevents repetition.\n\n4. Date intentionally. Quality over quantity. Each date adalah data about what you want dan don't want.\n\n5. Societal pressure optional. 'When will you marry?' doesn't require justification. Your timeline is your own.\n\nThe best relationship is the one you have with yourself.",
  moveon: "Moving on merupakan acceptance, not forgetting. Grief is nonlinear; healing requires active processing, not just time:\n\n1. Honor the grief. Suppression prolongs pain. Allow tears, anger, confusion. Emotions need expression to move through.\n\n2. No contact rule. Digital stalking, 'just checking' messages, accidental meetings. Each contact resets healing clock.\n\n3. Rebuild identity. Who are you outside this relationship? Rediscover atau invent new aspects of self.\n\n4. Reframe the narrative. Not 'wasted time' but 'learning experience'. Growth happened, even if relationship ended.\n\n5. New connections carefully. Don't rush untuk fill void. Rebound relationships often repeat patterns.\n\nClosing one door allows another to open.",

  // Karir Development
  promosi: "Career advancement requires strategic performance, visibility, dan capability demonstration. Do great work yang gets noticed:\n\n1. Exceed expectations consistently. Meet expectations keeps you employed; exceeding advances you. Track achievements dengan metrics.\n\n2. Build internal reputation. Cross-functional projects, mentoring, knowledge sharing. Visibility beyond immediate team.\n\n3. Develop next-level skills. Leadership, strategic thinking, communication. Show you can handle next role before officially in it.\n\n4. Communicate aspirations. Managers aren't mind readers. Express career goals; ask what needed untuk achieve them.\n\n5. Strategic patience. Promotions happen dalam organizational cycles. Persistent excellence plus timing equals advancement.\n\nPromotion is earned through demonstrated readiness.",
  pindah: "Job change merupakan career accelerator atau lateral move. Evaluate comprehensively sebelum jumping:\n\n1. Growth trajectory. Learning opportunities, promotion path, skill development. Stagnation kills careers.\n\n2. Culture assessment. Glassdoor, interviews dengan future teammates, observation during visit. Culture fit determines happiness.\n\n3. Total compensation. Base, bonus, equity, benefits, work-life balance. Run numbers; sometimes lower base equals higher total.\n\n4. Exit gracefully. Network preservation, handover documentation, gratitude. Burning bridges limits future options.\n\n5. Grass isn't always greener. Document why you're leaving; verify new role fixes those issues. Sometimes solve current problems instead.\n\nStrategic moves accelerate; reactive moves often disappoint.",
  remote: "Remote work merupakan flexibility privilege yang memerlukan intentional structure. Success requires discipline dan boundaries:\n\n1. Dedicated workspace. Separate dari relaxation areas. Physical boundary reinforces mental boundary.\n\n2. Routine matters. Start time, breaks, end time. Structure prevents work bleeding into all hours.\n\n3. Over-communication. Status updates, proactive reaching out, documented decisions. Visibility requires effort remotely.\n\n4. Social connection intentional. Virtual coffee chats, in-person meetups when possible. Isolation adalah remote work risk.\n\n5. Know when to stop. Shutdown ritual, leaving the 'office'. Without commute, boundaries blur easily.\n\nRemote work is freedom with responsibility.",
};

function findResponse(context, responses) {
  const lowerContext = context.toLowerCase();
  for (const [keyword, response] of Object.entries(responses)) {
    if (lowerContext.includes(keyword)) {
      return response;
    }
  }
  return null;
}

function generateMockCaption({ context }) {
  const cleanedContext = typeof context === "string" ? context.trim() : "";

  if (!cleanedContext) {
    return "Silakan ajukan pertanyaan atau ceritakan apa yang Anda butuhkan. Saya siap membantu dengan informasi yang saya miliki.";
  }

  // Cari response berdasarkan keyword
  const matchedResponse = findResponse(cleanedContext, ID_RESPONSES);

  if (matchedResponse) {
    return matchedResponse;
  }

  // Template response yang mengakui topik user untuk pertanyaan tidak terduga
  const topicWords = cleanedContext.split(/\s+/).slice(0, 3).join(" ");

  // Respons generik tapi kontekstual yang mengakui input user
  const genericResponses = [
    `Terima kasih telah berbagi tentang "${topicWords}". Meski saat ini layanan AI penuh, saya mengerti hal ini penting bagi Anda. Coba telusuri sumber terpercaya atau diskusikan dengan ahli di bidang tersebut.`,
    `Saya memahami Anda bertanya tentang "${topicWords}". Ini adalah topik yang menarik. Saat layanan AI kembali normal, saya bisa memberikan informasi lebih detail. Untuk saat ini, silakan cari referensi dari buku atau artikel terpercaya.`,
    `Anda menanyakan hal yang penting tentang "${topicWords}". Setiap pertanyaan layak mendapat jawaban yang baik. Mohon maaf saat ini sistem dalam mode terbatas. Coba ulangi pertanyaan nanti atau eksplorasi berbagai perspektif tentang topik ini.`,
    `Pertanyaan Anda tentang "${topicWords}" menunjukkan rasa ingin tahu yang bagus. Pengetahuan memang terus berkembang. Saat ini layanan sedang tidak tersedia penuh, tapi jangan berhenti mencari tahu dari sumber lain yang kredibel.`,
  ];

  // Pilih respons generik secara random
  const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * genericResponses.length);
  return genericResponses[randomIndex];
}

module.exports = {
  generateMockCaption,
};

